WEBVTT

00:01.836 --> 00:05.245
[cheerful jazz music]

00:05.397 --> 00:10.134
♪♪

00:32.533 --> 00:37.369
♪♪

00:56.965 --> 01:03.303
[alarm ringing]

01:03.455 --> 01:06.857
♪♪

01:10.554 --> 01:12.387
-Good morning.
-Morning, alexis.

01:12.406 --> 01:13.739
Welcome to new orleans, grace.

01:18.487 --> 01:21.154
I can't believe you're working
the day after flying in.

01:21.248 --> 01:22.656
You haven't even unpacked yet.

01:22.750 --> 01:25.325
Grace, are you ready?

01:25.477 --> 01:27.644
Absolutely.

01:27.663 --> 01:28.829
Why, thank you.

01:28.981 --> 01:30.089
Mmm.

01:30.316 --> 01:32.816
Mmm?

01:32.835 --> 01:35.168
-Is that bourbon?
-You have a big day.

01:35.321 --> 01:36.261
Figured you could
use a little lagniappe.

01:36.488 --> 01:38.263
A la-- who?

01:38.415 --> 01:39.823
It means
a little something extra.

01:39.842 --> 01:41.583
-Like bourbon in your coffee.
-Alexis!

01:41.602 --> 01:43.677
Relax, it's cajun eggnog coffee.

01:43.771 --> 01:45.253
The strongest thing in
there is the bourbon extract.

01:45.272 --> 01:46.847
Mm-hm.

01:46.999 --> 01:48.181
Cajun eggnog coffee.

01:48.275 --> 01:49.850
[laughing]

01:50.002 --> 01:51.835
Definitely not
in kansas anymore.

01:51.854 --> 01:53.687
Kansas is just about the only
place you haven't lived.

01:53.839 --> 01:55.263
Oh, not true. Not true.

01:55.357 --> 01:57.674
Remember, about five years ago,

01:57.767 --> 01:59.025
I did that
renovation in topeka.

01:59.120 --> 02:00.786
-Of course, you did.
-Yes.

02:00.937 --> 02:02.604
Well, I'm glad I finally
got you to new orleans.

02:02.698 --> 02:04.623
For a little while anyway.

02:04.774 --> 02:06.274
Ah, I'm waiting to hear
about this job in toronto,

02:06.293 --> 02:07.534
So keep your fingers crossed.

02:07.628 --> 02:08.869
Of course you are.

02:09.021 --> 02:10.871
Oh, come on, you know me.

02:11.023 --> 02:12.614
I don't stay in
one place for too long.

02:12.633 --> 02:14.133
The glamorous life
of a freelance architect.

02:14.360 --> 02:15.801
Yes, ma'am.

02:15.952 --> 02:17.711
-Come on.
-Okay.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.597
[cheerful music]

02:27.890 --> 02:29.706
What ya looking at?

02:29.725 --> 02:31.984
My client just
sent me these pictures

02:32.211 --> 02:34.135
Of her family
celebrating christmas.

02:34.229 --> 02:35.712
Aw, it's so cute.

02:35.731 --> 02:37.823
I know.

02:38.050 --> 02:40.901
I always get these
boring paint by number projects.

02:40.995 --> 02:43.570
And I am so excited
to be doing a family home.

02:43.664 --> 02:45.071
Oh, what she do again?

02:45.224 --> 02:46.740
She's some praline mogul.

02:46.892 --> 02:48.241
You're working
for loretta brown?

02:48.394 --> 02:50.560
You know who she is?

02:50.579 --> 02:53.005
Ah, she is only
a new orleans icon.

02:53.156 --> 02:55.674
Well, yes,
she is the first black woman

02:55.901 --> 02:58.493
To own her own confectionery
shop in new orleans.

02:58.512 --> 03:00.679
And I am redoing her family home

03:00.830 --> 03:04.165
For a lifetime of christmases
and pralines baking.

03:04.185 --> 03:05.575
Aw, a lifetime of christmases.

03:05.594 --> 03:07.686
I get it.

03:07.913 --> 03:10.338
You know, you are
really obsessed with christmas.

03:10.432 --> 03:12.933
Hey, I can appreciate it, okay?

03:13.027 --> 03:14.267
You know,<i> white christmas</i> was
written by one of ours.

03:14.361 --> 03:15.694
What? A white person?

03:15.845 --> 03:18.030
-A jewish person.
-Okay.

03:19.700 --> 03:22.759
Hey, I know you like to do
the whole solo christmas thing.

03:22.852 --> 03:24.686
Yes, I do.

03:24.705 --> 03:26.688
I enjoy sitting on
my couch in my pajamas,

03:26.782 --> 03:28.373
Watching christmas movies,

03:28.600 --> 03:30.042
Eating those little
peanut butter santas

03:30.193 --> 03:32.026
And buying myself
a ridiculously expensive gift

03:32.046 --> 03:33.286
That I don't need.

03:33.439 --> 03:35.214
By yourself?

03:35.365 --> 03:37.607
Yes, and I know it may
sound sad to some people,

03:37.701 --> 03:39.943
But hey, I don't
have to worry about

03:40.036 --> 03:41.720
Anybody stealing
my christmas candy.

03:41.871 --> 03:43.463
Hey, you're coming to
my hanukkahmas party, right?

03:43.615 --> 03:45.039
It's the Friday
before christmas.

03:45.059 --> 03:46.874
-Hanukkahmas?
-Mm-hm. Are you in?

03:46.894 --> 03:49.619
You know, I...
I may have to work.

03:49.713 --> 03:52.289
Ugh, classic
grace hill brush-off.

03:52.307 --> 03:54.233
I know it well.

03:54.460 --> 03:56.460
Everyone is not
a social butterfly like you.

03:56.553 --> 03:58.144
Okay, well,
it's kind of at the house,

03:58.297 --> 03:59.479
So may not have a choice.

03:59.573 --> 04:00.572
Are you serious?

04:00.799 --> 04:02.482
Sorry!

04:02.634 --> 04:05.469
Oh, come here,
let's go this way.

04:05.487 --> 04:07.153
Right here,
right here, right here.

04:07.248 --> 04:08.896
Just-- just look normal.

04:08.991 --> 04:11.667
Oh, look at this tree.
This is so nice.

04:15.071 --> 04:17.831
-Was that anthony from college?
-Yes.

04:17.925 --> 04:19.907
And we hid from him because why?

04:19.927 --> 04:21.651
Because I have a big day

04:21.745 --> 04:23.578
And I don't
need any distractions.

04:23.597 --> 04:25.655
You had the biggest
crush on him in college,

04:25.674 --> 04:27.491
So you would
definitely be distracted.

04:27.509 --> 04:30.327
-No, I didn't.
-Hmm.

04:30.420 --> 04:32.345
All right, maybe yes, I did.
Just a little bit.

04:32.498 --> 04:34.439
What happened with you guys?

04:34.591 --> 04:37.684
Well, you know, we were
in almost every class together

04:37.778 --> 04:39.836
And super competitive.

04:39.929 --> 04:41.947
However, I did think
at the end of senior year,

04:42.098 --> 04:43.765
We maybe had
a little romantic spark,

04:43.859 --> 04:45.692
But then
my parents' accident happened

04:45.844 --> 04:47.286
And we just lost touch.

04:47.513 --> 04:49.788
-Yeah, that was a tough time.
-Yeah.

04:49.939 --> 04:54.126
Man, I cannot believe it's been
ten years since I've seen him.

04:54.353 --> 04:55.535
Really?

04:55.629 --> 04:57.354
He emailed me a couple of times,

04:57.447 --> 04:58.780
But I just
didn't want to bother him

04:58.874 --> 05:00.782
With my family stuff, so...

05:00.801 --> 05:03.302
Then, after that, I went
on my internship to london.

05:03.453 --> 05:05.787
And then moved to
frankfurt and okay, I see now.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.864
But I wouldn't worry about it.

05:07.957 --> 05:08.974
He'll probably
never see you again.

05:09.125 --> 05:11.217
[laughing]

05:11.312 --> 05:13.553
Famous last words.

05:13.647 --> 05:16.373
[light cheerful music]

05:16.391 --> 05:18.542
Alexis:
I got all these decorations.

05:18.560 --> 05:20.968
It's going to be so cute.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.804
And I am going to be
facetiming with [indistinct],

05:22.823 --> 05:25.048
But with turkey, because--
oh, we're here.

05:25.141 --> 05:27.050
-402, barrack street, right?
-Yeah.

05:27.143 --> 05:28.827
Thank you so much for
walking me the whole way.

05:28.978 --> 05:30.737
You want me to
wait for you nearby?

05:30.831 --> 05:32.664
-Please.
-Of course.

05:32.816 --> 05:35.983
Oh, and it's prah-line,
not pray-line, trust me.

05:36.003 --> 05:37.502
-Prah-line, got it!
-Okay.

05:37.729 --> 05:39.171
Okay.

05:39.322 --> 05:42.415
Oh, this is such
a cute, little area.

05:42.568 --> 05:45.752
This house is so beautiful.

05:45.846 --> 05:48.513
It's perfect. Why would
anyone want to renovate this?

05:48.740 --> 05:49.848
Grace hill.

05:51.243 --> 05:53.167
Small world.

05:53.261 --> 05:54.594
Hey, how are you?

05:54.746 --> 05:58.264
Wow. Anthony brown.

05:58.417 --> 05:59.274
Please.

06:00.861 --> 06:03.344
Uh...What a surprise.

06:03.364 --> 06:05.030
What are you, um, doing here?

06:05.181 --> 06:07.032
Surprise, huh?

06:07.183 --> 06:08.533
Because I'm pretty
sure you saw me back there.

06:08.685 --> 06:10.351
That was you?

06:10.371 --> 06:12.445
What are you
doing in new orleans?

06:12.539 --> 06:13.947
Actually, I'm here
for a small renovation gig.

06:14.099 --> 06:15.207
Really?

06:15.434 --> 06:17.784
That's great. Yeah.

06:17.936 --> 06:19.119
So, what are you
doing around here?

06:19.213 --> 06:21.287
Getting inspiration or--

06:21.440 --> 06:24.549
No. No, this is
my actual renovation gig.

06:24.776 --> 06:26.033
This house?

06:26.128 --> 06:28.053
-Yeah.
-You sure?

06:28.280 --> 06:30.280
I mean, unless there's
another 402 barrack street

06:30.298 --> 06:32.282
In new orleans
that I don't know about.

06:32.375 --> 06:34.559
I'm sorry. The reason I'm asking

06:34.711 --> 06:36.453
Is because I'm doing
the renovations on this house.

06:36.471 --> 06:37.879
-You?
-Yeah.

06:37.898 --> 06:40.640
So, if I'm doing the renovations

06:40.792 --> 06:43.068
And you're
doing the renovations,

06:43.219 --> 06:44.961
That means...

06:44.980 --> 06:47.054
Well, so come on.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.633
Our meeting was supposed
to start a full minute ago.

06:49.651 --> 06:51.818
Get on in here.

06:51.970 --> 06:52.744
Oh, guess we'll be
working together then.

06:57.918 --> 06:59.918
Yeah.

07:06.318 --> 07:08.985
Welcome to my home.

07:09.078 --> 07:10.578
It's so nice to
meet you, miss grace,

07:10.597 --> 07:12.672
In person that is.

07:12.766 --> 07:14.340
Such a pleasure to
meet you too, miss loretta.

07:14.493 --> 07:16.268
Oh, no, no.

07:16.495 --> 07:17.602
Everybody who walks
through that door is family.

07:17.754 --> 07:19.162
And we hug them as family.

07:19.181 --> 07:20.346
Don't we, baby?

07:20.441 --> 07:21.831
[laughing]

07:21.850 --> 07:22.941
Oh, baby.

07:23.092 --> 07:24.943
Baby, huh?

07:25.170 --> 07:27.520
Didn't he tell you
that he's my grandson?

07:27.673 --> 07:30.356
Your grandson-- your grandso--
this is-- you're her grandson?

07:30.451 --> 07:31.283
Ever since I was born.

07:31.510 --> 07:33.935
[laughs]

07:33.954 --> 07:36.788
Well, miss loretta,
you didn't include him

07:36.940 --> 07:38.531
In any of the pictures
that you sent me.

07:38.625 --> 07:40.292
You sent pictures?

07:40.519 --> 07:42.535
Grandma, can I speak
to you, please?

07:42.629 --> 07:44.463
Of course.

07:44.690 --> 07:46.356
My darling,
why don't you help yourself

07:46.449 --> 07:47.874
To some pralines
in the living room?

07:47.968 --> 07:49.526
They're my specialty.

07:49.544 --> 07:50.969
-Thank you.
-So good.

07:55.200 --> 07:57.124
I'm sure I don't know why

07:57.144 --> 07:58.810
Are you looking at
your grandma like that.

07:59.037 --> 08:01.037
You didn't tell me
I was going to have a partner.

08:01.130 --> 08:02.964
Didn't I?
Must have slipped my mind.

08:02.983 --> 08:04.724
Grandma, you are the smartest
woman I've ever met.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.710
Nothing slips your mind.

08:06.803 --> 08:08.487
I thought you could
use some help, that's all.

08:08.714 --> 08:11.064
And she seems like
the perfect person to give it.

08:11.158 --> 08:13.733
For the record, I am capable
of doing this on my own.

08:13.827 --> 08:17.496
And if I hate the designs
you two come up with, you can.

08:17.647 --> 08:20.499
But right now, you have
to at least try it with grace.

08:20.726 --> 08:23.293
This is what I want.

08:24.746 --> 08:26.153
Okay, I'll try.

08:26.248 --> 08:29.399
-[loretta sighs]
-I'll try.

08:29.492 --> 08:31.659
-Good.
-Grace--she's a good architect.

08:31.753 --> 08:34.012
We're just very different.

08:34.163 --> 08:36.014
You know what they say
about opposites, don't you?

08:42.581 --> 08:44.748
Oh, oh, oh.

08:44.766 --> 08:49.510
I'm so sorry.
They are just so good.

08:49.530 --> 08:53.014
Of course. No one can
resist a miss loretta treat.

08:53.108 --> 08:55.258
That's a praline promise.

08:55.277 --> 08:57.594
Why don't you and anthony
take a look around my house

08:57.687 --> 08:59.596
And start coming up
with some ideas?

08:59.689 --> 09:01.114
Don't you want
to brief us first?

09:01.208 --> 09:03.024
I'll be brief.

09:03.118 --> 09:04.876
Make the house look phenomenal.

09:06.438 --> 09:07.212
Okay.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.843
-Should we, uh--
-let's start upstairs.

09:15.447 --> 09:17.013
Oh, okay.

09:20.952 --> 09:22.227
Anthony: So the house
was built in 1888,

09:22.454 --> 09:25.230
And it hasn't been updated
since the 1920s,

09:25.457 --> 09:27.048
So you can see
how badly this reno is needed.

09:27.142 --> 09:28.808
The first thing I want to do

09:28.902 --> 09:30.143
Is probably blow out
these walls down here.

09:30.237 --> 09:31.795
Oh no, no, no, no.

09:31.888 --> 09:33.296
This is a beautiful,
historic home.

09:33.315 --> 09:34.981
You can't just
go blowing out walls.

09:35.133 --> 09:36.741
Well, up until
a few minutes ago,

09:36.968 --> 09:38.410
We weren't doing
anything, were we?

09:38.561 --> 09:39.986
[laughing]

09:40.080 --> 09:43.397
Who got coal in his stocking?

09:43.491 --> 09:46.084
You're afraid of me stealing
your spotlight, aren't you?

09:46.311 --> 09:47.660
Grace, no one's
going to steal my spotlight.

09:47.754 --> 09:49.162
Oh, yeah, no one but me.

09:49.314 --> 09:50.830
It's just like old times.

09:50.982 --> 09:52.665
-Old times?
-Mm-hm.

09:52.818 --> 09:54.593
Back when I used to
beat you at everything.

09:54.820 --> 09:56.243
You think you could
stop teasing me long enough

09:56.263 --> 09:57.578
For us to get some work done?

09:57.598 --> 10:00.490
Maybe when it's no longer fun.

10:00.508 --> 10:02.492
It's very mature.

10:02.510 --> 10:04.251
Listen, I've got to
be honest with you, okay?

10:04.271 --> 10:06.087
This house, it needs to be nice.

10:06.181 --> 10:08.181
I'm talking next level here.

10:08.333 --> 10:10.275
And it is my family's house,
so I'm kind of feeling like

10:10.426 --> 10:11.835
You should let me
take the lead on this.

10:11.928 --> 10:13.612
Yeah, but your grandma hired me.

10:13.763 --> 10:16.673
And I heard that.
But it is my family's legacy.

10:16.691 --> 10:19.284
And I was hired to do a job,
and I'm going to do it.

10:19.435 --> 10:21.361
-Grace--
-okay, listen, anthony.

10:21.513 --> 10:23.121
Why don't we pick
this up tomorrow?

10:23.348 --> 10:24.848
I'm going to give you
a little bit of time

10:24.866 --> 10:26.182
To get your mind right.

10:26.201 --> 10:28.351
That's the door, right?

10:28.370 --> 10:30.036
I'll be going this way.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.537
[grace sighs]

10:31.690 --> 10:33.690
Just like old times.

10:33.708 --> 10:36.450
I mean, she has
this beautiful home

10:36.470 --> 10:38.361
With these historic flourishes

10:38.380 --> 10:39.879
And he just wants
to tear it all down.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.473
Can you believe that?

10:41.700 --> 10:43.475
What I can't believe

10:43.702 --> 10:45.051
Is that you didn't
introduce me to miss loretta.

10:45.203 --> 10:48.129
-I'm obsessed with her.
-Not now, alexis.

10:48.148 --> 10:50.131
Anthony really
got under your skin.

10:50.150 --> 10:51.966
Do you know that he
doesn't want to work with me?

10:52.060 --> 10:53.726
And you know, quite frankly,

10:53.879 --> 10:55.302
I'm not sure if
I want to work with him

10:55.322 --> 10:56.488
Right now, either.

10:56.639 --> 10:58.156
-He's just so--
-hot?

10:58.383 --> 11:00.158
-No, he's so--
-devastatingly handsome?

11:00.309 --> 11:02.402
No, he's--

11:02.554 --> 11:03.736
Better than any christmas
present santa ever brought you?

11:03.830 --> 11:05.238
Alexis, stop.

11:05.332 --> 11:08.074
This is my dream job, alexis.

11:08.226 --> 11:10.484
I just want to create a home

11:10.504 --> 11:14.339
For this family that is
warm and loving and inviting.

11:14.566 --> 11:18.234
And he just wants to
make it cold and unfeeling.

11:18.253 --> 11:20.236
I think you both
want the same things.

11:20.329 --> 11:21.421
You're just going
about it different ways.

11:21.515 --> 11:23.998
I don't know about that.

11:24.017 --> 11:26.592
Try to stick it out.
Help him see your point of view.

11:26.745 --> 11:30.171
Who knows? Maybe you could
learn something from him too.

11:30.265 --> 11:32.524
Ha! That would be a miracle.

11:32.675 --> 11:35.601
And what better time for
a miracle than the holidays?

11:35.696 --> 11:36.920
Oh, my goodness.

11:36.938 --> 11:40.014
[alexis laughs]

11:40.108 --> 11:42.534
[jazz music playing]

11:47.874 --> 11:49.949
-Anthony: I'm here to pull--
-chris: Okay, I'm pulling.

11:50.043 --> 11:52.860
Can't believe y'all still
haven't decorated this tree yet.

11:52.879 --> 11:55.362
It's kind of hard to
do when the guy who's, you know,

11:55.382 --> 11:57.957
Best at untangling lights
is always working.

11:58.051 --> 12:00.109
Chris, you keep this up,

12:00.203 --> 12:01.277
He might never
leave the office again.

12:01.296 --> 12:02.703
Thank you, mom.

12:02.797 --> 12:04.464
But he is right, you know.

12:04.558 --> 12:06.725
You too?

12:06.952 --> 12:08.468
Anthony, we have not
seen you since thanksgiving.

12:08.620 --> 12:10.453
You always hold up in
that workplace of yours.

12:10.546 --> 12:11.621
Yeah, because I'm trying
to build something great,

12:11.639 --> 12:13.639
Like grandma did.

12:13.734 --> 12:15.734
And I got some new ideas, too.

12:15.961 --> 12:18.144
Yeah, like your scheme
with the shop.

12:18.238 --> 12:20.630
No, that's-- that's not
a scheme. That's a plan.

12:20.648 --> 12:23.299
One day that stubborn of a woman
is going to let me do it, too.

12:23.392 --> 12:24.909
Look, if we modernized the shop,

12:25.061 --> 12:26.745
Gave her some
bells and whistles,

12:26.896 --> 12:27.987
She wouldn't
have to work so hard.

12:28.139 --> 12:29.639
Hey, man, I'm with you.

12:29.732 --> 12:30.990
I would love some
new bells and whistles

12:31.142 --> 12:32.399
At the shop myself.

12:32.494 --> 12:33.752
-Thank you.
-Dope, man.

12:33.979 --> 12:35.253
Anthony, you know
your grandmother.

12:35.404 --> 12:37.255
The old ways are the best.

12:37.482 --> 12:38.923
Mm-hm.

12:39.075 --> 12:40.817
But, uh...

12:40.910 --> 12:42.502
It's about that girl,
though, isn't it?

12:42.596 --> 12:44.596
The one grandma hired.

12:44.823 --> 12:45.764
Which girl?

12:48.159 --> 12:50.176
Anthony? What girl?

12:50.328 --> 12:51.770
You got a big mouth.

12:51.997 --> 12:53.663
Mom, I don't have
time for some setup,

12:53.756 --> 12:55.848
I got to focus on this redesign.

12:56.001 --> 12:58.684
Grace is just another architect
that grandma hired, okay?

12:58.779 --> 13:01.337
Let me talk about the shop.
Let's keep it at the shop, okay?

13:01.430 --> 13:03.006
Well, if it's
so important to you,

13:03.024 --> 13:04.507
Why don't you
show your grandmother

13:04.600 --> 13:05.950
That you respect
the old traditions?

13:06.177 --> 13:07.952
Meaning?

13:08.179 --> 13:10.288
What if--

13:10.515 --> 13:12.791
What if you made
her pralines from scratch?

13:12.942 --> 13:14.942
[giggling]

13:14.961 --> 13:17.854
-Oh, grandma's pralines.
-Mm-hm.

13:17.947 --> 13:19.464
-The secret pralines?
-Mm-hm.

13:19.691 --> 13:21.633
The secret recipe
that only grandma

13:21.860 --> 13:23.526
And one other person
at the shop knows about?

13:23.619 --> 13:24.877
I didn't say it
was going to be easy.

13:25.030 --> 13:26.863
It's not.

13:26.956 --> 13:28.289
But if you want
things to change, it--

13:28.383 --> 13:30.475
It might not be a bad idea

13:30.626 --> 13:32.143
If you show her that you
know where it all started, huh?

13:34.130 --> 13:36.539
Oh, I got to get
to the store. Here.

13:36.632 --> 13:38.875
-Who's working too hard now?
-Only be a minute.

13:38.968 --> 13:41.210
Mom, would you let me
know if daryl dropped off

13:41.229 --> 13:43.046
That last stack
of pralines, please?

13:43.064 --> 13:44.805
Yeah, folks need to
get those by christmas.

13:44.825 --> 13:45.990
Yes, they do. Remember what
happened last christmas?

13:46.217 --> 13:47.900
[laughs]

13:47.994 --> 13:49.886
You got 20 bags of pralines
at the store stocked up?

13:49.979 --> 13:51.312
Yeah, and then we
had to go door-to-door

13:51.406 --> 13:52.722
On christmas eve.

13:52.740 --> 13:53.573
-That hurt that boy.
-[laughs]

13:53.667 --> 13:55.166
You know daryl, right?

13:55.393 --> 13:57.076
Not really.

13:57.228 --> 13:58.652
If he forgets
another stack of pralines,

13:58.746 --> 13:59.987
There will be no more daryl.

14:00.081 --> 14:01.914
Oh, calm down, mr. Boss man.

14:02.067 --> 14:02.799
-Give me a kiss.
-Mwah.

14:04.736 --> 14:06.678
Give me a kiss. Bye.

14:06.905 --> 14:11.165
[soft festive music]

14:11.184 --> 14:12.517
Anthony: You got a big mouth.

14:12.744 --> 14:14.168
[giggles]

14:14.187 --> 14:15.428
Don't worry man,
I won't tell her.

14:15.580 --> 14:16.837
Won't tell her what?

14:16.931 --> 14:18.356
That grace hill is the girl

14:18.507 --> 14:20.416
Who you had
a crush on in college.

14:20.435 --> 14:22.694
-Hey, hey, man, keep it down.
-What is the problem?

14:22.845 --> 14:24.696
I don't want grandma to hear.
You know she'll meddle.

14:24.847 --> 14:27.773
-Grandma already knows.
-What?

14:27.868 --> 14:30.535
Yeah, I told her when I saw
grace in your alumni magazine.

14:30.762 --> 14:32.370
Why else do you think
she brought her here?

14:32.521 --> 14:34.097
Well, I don't have time
for some setup, all right?

14:34.190 --> 14:35.707
I just want to
focus on this redesign.

14:35.934 --> 14:37.542
Yeah, and I'm gonna
let you handle that.

14:37.693 --> 14:39.619
But I am going to
ask you one last time,

14:39.713 --> 14:41.454
Just so you don't forget
because it's very important.

14:41.606 --> 14:43.623
Yes, I will pick
charlene up from the airport.

14:43.775 --> 14:45.216
-On time.
-On time.

14:45.368 --> 14:47.051
-No work emergencies.
-Chris.

14:47.203 --> 14:48.961
Just asking.
And keep it quiet,

14:49.055 --> 14:50.371
It's supposed to be
a surprise for jordan.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.706
Hey, I got this.

14:52.800 --> 14:55.184
This will be a christmas
our family will never forget.

14:58.123 --> 15:02.975
[festive music playing]

15:03.069 --> 15:06.979
♪♪

15:07.132 --> 15:10.149
Inspiration, inspiration,

15:10.301 --> 15:12.485
I just need
a little bit of inspiration.

15:12.579 --> 15:14.061
Mm-hm.

15:14.155 --> 15:18.157
[festive jazz music playing]

15:18.309 --> 15:22.337
♪♪

15:58.959 --> 16:03.211
[bell tolling]

16:13.381 --> 16:16.199
-Excuse me, miss?
-Hi, yes.

16:16.217 --> 16:17.717
-Can I ask you a question?
-Um, okay.

16:17.811 --> 16:20.203
Okay.

16:20.221 --> 16:24.040
Well, it's not so much
a question as a comment.

16:24.133 --> 16:26.542
My teacher says
I'm supposed to say it

16:26.561 --> 16:28.227
When I have a comment
instead of a question.

16:28.321 --> 16:30.396
Okay.

16:30.490 --> 16:34.066
I think you forgot
all the people in your picture.

16:34.160 --> 16:36.385
You know what?

16:36.404 --> 16:39.555
You are absolutely right.

16:39.574 --> 16:42.333
So could you help me out
and draw some for me, please?

16:47.065 --> 16:50.324
Hey, jordan.
Please don't bother this lady.

16:50.418 --> 16:52.401
Hey, uncle anthony.

16:52.495 --> 16:54.403
I can't seem to
get rid of you, can I?

16:54.497 --> 16:55.905
I'm sorry, is she bothering you?

16:55.923 --> 16:58.182
Absolutely not.

16:58.334 --> 17:00.685
I'm getting an art lesson
from my new assistant.

17:00.912 --> 17:02.762
At least someone
in your family appreciates

17:02.856 --> 17:04.764
Historic design.

17:04.858 --> 17:06.766
That's very funny.

17:06.918 --> 17:08.434
Hey, jordan,
you remember we talked about

17:08.586 --> 17:10.086
Not talking to strangers?

17:10.179 --> 17:13.197
We aren't strangers.
This is, um...

17:13.424 --> 17:15.015
-[whispers] grace.
-Yeah, this is grace.

17:15.035 --> 17:17.610
And I'm painting her picture.

17:17.762 --> 17:20.096
She forgot the people
and the christmas trees.

17:20.114 --> 17:21.931
There aren't any
christmas trees, jordan.

17:21.949 --> 17:23.766
It's a christmas picture.

17:23.785 --> 17:25.951
It needs christmas trees.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.880
Yeah, uncle anthony,
where is your imagination?

17:29.107 --> 17:32.032
Well, my architectural
table's mighty cozy.

17:32.126 --> 17:33.534
Have you come up
with any designs yet?

17:33.553 --> 17:35.035
Oh yeah.

17:35.129 --> 17:37.055
-Nice.
-If you're looking for

17:37.206 --> 17:38.723
A christmas-themed house
from the 1800s.

17:38.874 --> 17:40.132
Have these two
been bothering you?

17:40.226 --> 17:42.134
[grace laughs]

17:42.287 --> 17:44.303
Well, jordan,
your great-granddaughter here,

17:44.397 --> 17:46.122
Has been an absolute delight.

17:46.215 --> 17:47.732
Your grandson,
on the other hand...

17:47.959 --> 17:49.308
Did you hire her
just to have somebody else

17:49.402 --> 17:50.793
To pick at me?

17:50.886 --> 17:53.129
Grace, don't pay him any mind.

17:53.222 --> 17:54.964
The boy's been
working mighty hard.

17:55.057 --> 17:56.982
Jordan's mom, charlene,
is in turkey,

17:57.077 --> 17:59.077
So we're all helping out
while her dad goes shopping

17:59.304 --> 18:00.986
For some g-I-f-t-s.

18:01.081 --> 18:04.398
Grandma, you know I can spell.

18:04.417 --> 18:06.417
-[laughter]
-I know you can.

18:06.569 --> 18:09.420
-So, turkey?
-She's in the marines.

18:09.647 --> 18:11.814
Wow, your mama
sounds pretty awesome.

18:11.833 --> 18:14.483
Yeah, I miss her, though.

18:14.502 --> 18:16.094
-I wish she were here.
-Yeah.

18:17.764 --> 18:18.930
Can you come to lunch, grace?

18:19.157 --> 18:20.581
Oh.

18:20.675 --> 18:22.916
That's a great idea, jordan.

18:23.010 --> 18:26.162
Grace, I made a sweet potato
pie with a praline topping.

18:26.255 --> 18:28.180
Can't even get one
of those in my shop.

18:28.333 --> 18:29.348
Family only, honey.

18:29.442 --> 18:32.426
I-- I'd hate to intrude.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.947
Oh, grandma always says
that family is who you choose.

18:36.098 --> 18:39.283
If you pick us,
then you can come.

18:39.510 --> 18:42.528
Hey grace, don't feel
like you are obligated to.

18:42.680 --> 18:44.789
Sure, I'd love to come.

18:45.016 --> 18:46.124
Come on.

18:49.945 --> 18:52.130
Okay, so you like art,
sweetheart?

18:57.119 --> 18:59.044
You know,
some people might say it's fate,

18:59.139 --> 19:00.880
Her being here today.

19:00.974 --> 19:03.199
Yeah?

19:03.217 --> 19:06.126
Some people might say
she's got a very good guidebook.

19:06.146 --> 19:08.795
You'll never get your
work done talking like that.

19:08.815 --> 19:11.482
If you keep sniping at her,
she's going to leave.

19:11.709 --> 19:14.318
So, I think you
should try another approach.

19:14.470 --> 19:16.154
Okay, well, what approach
do you suggest, grandma?

19:16.305 --> 19:19.882
Opening your pretty heart.

19:19.901 --> 19:22.218
Big talk coming from a woman
who's been single for 25 years.

19:22.311 --> 19:23.903
I know you didn't just go there.

19:24.055 --> 19:25.312
Let me say something to you.

19:25.406 --> 19:27.981
I've been working for 30 years.

19:28.001 --> 19:31.076
Taking care of my business
and my family, on my own.

19:31.171 --> 19:33.004
Come on, grandma, you know
I didn't mean it like that.

19:33.231 --> 19:34.747
Okay, let me tell
you what we can do.

19:34.899 --> 19:37.491
If you open your heart,
I'll open mine.

19:37.510 --> 19:38.634
But it's your move first, boo.

19:41.923 --> 19:43.347
Okay, I'll try.

19:43.574 --> 19:44.682
You'll what?

19:44.909 --> 19:46.575
Try?

19:46.669 --> 19:47.927
Try what?
You better do the darn thing.

19:48.079 --> 19:50.095
Talkin' 'bout "try."

19:50.248 --> 19:52.106
♪♪

19:56.087 --> 19:57.844
♪♪

19:57.864 --> 20:00.272
Hi, mr. Anthony.

20:00.425 --> 20:02.450
Oh, hi, rose. I love that dress.

20:04.520 --> 20:07.354
Oh, you're pretty popular.

20:07.373 --> 20:09.114
That's just how new orleans is.

20:09.209 --> 20:11.267
You know, you can't swing
an ornament in this town

20:11.360 --> 20:12.601
Without hitting
somebody you know.

20:12.620 --> 20:15.271
Oh, I am just surprised

20:15.289 --> 20:17.548
That you have gotten out
long enough to meet somebody.

20:17.775 --> 20:20.793
You were very
serious in college.

20:20.945 --> 20:25.965
Yeah, I know I... I've been
very intense and I am sorry.

20:26.117 --> 20:28.467
Wow.

20:28.619 --> 20:30.561
Christmas really is
the time for miracles.

20:33.048 --> 20:34.232
How about a fresh start?

20:35.643 --> 20:37.884
Okay, but how do I know

20:37.904 --> 20:39.628
You're not going to run out
before the job's done?

20:39.647 --> 20:41.464
I heard you've
been all over the world.

20:41.557 --> 20:43.482
Oh, have you been
checking up on me?

20:43.576 --> 20:45.726
Social media.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.561
Ah, you have
been checking up on me.

20:47.580 --> 20:49.396
[grace laughing]

20:49.415 --> 20:52.416
Well, I've been
to london and paris,

20:52.568 --> 20:55.144
New york, frankfurt.

20:55.237 --> 20:57.480
I do really love traveling.

20:57.498 --> 21:00.240
But I have to say,
seeing you with your family

21:00.260 --> 21:03.076
And your grandmother's
house has made me

21:03.096 --> 21:05.746
A little bit jealous.
-I don't know.

21:05.840 --> 21:07.914
Traveling all over the world
doesn't sound that bad.

21:07.934 --> 21:10.175
Don't worry,
I'm not going anywhere

21:10.328 --> 21:12.661
Until at least I finish
your grandmother's house, okay?

21:12.755 --> 21:14.605
Oh, my goodness, decorations.

21:18.093 --> 21:21.595
You know, this is
my first time on a streetcar.

21:21.614 --> 21:24.031
-Really?
-Yes, and it is exhilarating.

21:25.510 --> 21:27.343
I don't think I've ever heard

21:27.361 --> 21:29.528
Anybody use that word
for a streetcar before.

21:29.622 --> 21:31.030
You could jog faster
than this thing goes.

21:31.124 --> 21:32.865
[grace laughs]

21:33.017 --> 21:36.627
No, but there's
just something...

21:36.779 --> 21:39.964
[sighs] just charming about
this old-school feel.

21:40.191 --> 21:42.207
It's, you know,
kind of romantic.

21:42.302 --> 21:44.951
My grandfather used
to tell me this story

21:45.046 --> 21:47.379
About a guy who won the love
of his life on a streetcar.

21:47.532 --> 21:49.456
Oh.

21:49.475 --> 21:51.700
Yeah, apparently
she was into animals.

21:51.719 --> 21:53.644
So, he filled
the streetcar with animals

21:53.796 --> 21:55.554
From the audubon zoo
and drove it to her house.

21:55.648 --> 21:57.815
[grace giggles]

21:58.818 --> 22:00.225
[brake screeching]

22:00.378 --> 22:02.227
Oh.

22:02.322 --> 22:04.046
-[grace laughing]
-still think it's romantic?

22:04.139 --> 22:06.157
I mean, it's got potential.

22:09.829 --> 22:12.163
[soft orchestral music playing]

22:22.066 --> 22:26.493
[laughing and chatting
in distance]

22:26.587 --> 22:27.762
-You okay?
-Huh?

22:29.849 --> 22:34.093
It, um, sounds like you have
a pretty big family, huh?

22:34.245 --> 22:36.412
Yeah, but don't worry.

22:36.505 --> 22:37.521
They're all
a lot nicer than I am.

22:37.748 --> 22:40.416
Hm.

22:40.434 --> 22:42.084
Well, I haven't been
to a family thing since...

22:42.177 --> 22:43.027
Um, I'm just feeling nervous.

22:43.178 --> 22:44.937
Well, don't.

22:45.089 --> 22:47.347
None of my family's
cooking's that bad.

22:47.367 --> 22:49.200
Unless my brother
made potato salad.

22:49.351 --> 22:55.614
[indistinct chatting]

22:55.708 --> 22:57.375
Oh, they're here!

22:57.526 --> 22:59.043
[laughing]

22:59.194 --> 23:00.544
They're here!

23:00.696 --> 23:03.196
-Hi.
-Hi.

23:03.290 --> 23:06.032
Oh, hi! You must be grace.

23:06.052 --> 23:07.551
Yeah. I met you
at the graduation,

23:07.703 --> 23:10.704
-I'm anthony's mom, tina.
-It's so nice to see you again.

23:10.723 --> 23:12.706
I'm just
stopping by for a second.

23:12.800 --> 23:14.950
-Oh, no, no, you just got here.
-Oh, no. Come on in.

23:14.969 --> 23:16.619
There is plenty
of food for everybody.

23:16.637 --> 23:17.953
Right, and I hope
my brother's not giving you

23:17.972 --> 23:19.622
Too much trouble.

23:19.715 --> 23:21.232
Oh, no,
I'm not worried about her,

23:21.459 --> 23:23.049
I know she can
stick it right back to him.

23:23.069 --> 23:27.738
All right, family. Let's all
take hands and say grace.

23:31.819 --> 23:32.985
-Grace?
-Hmm?

23:33.137 --> 23:35.896
Would you like to do the honors?

23:35.915 --> 23:39.808
Oh, I'm-- I'm just a guest.
I-- I couldn't--

23:39.827 --> 23:41.752
You sit at this table, baby,
and you're family.

23:42.997 --> 23:43.921
Family?

23:45.925 --> 23:47.149
[grace sighing]

23:47.242 --> 23:49.760
Oh, um, but-- but I, um...

23:53.248 --> 23:54.323
Oh, you know what, hold on--

23:54.416 --> 23:57.435
Is that my phone? I'm sorry.

23:57.586 --> 24:01.180
Oh, I am so sorry,
I really have to take this call.

24:01.332 --> 24:03.924
-Is it--
-no worries, yeah,

24:03.943 --> 24:05.501
We'll be fine.
Go and take the call.

24:05.519 --> 24:06.610
Thank you.

24:16.456 --> 24:18.530
Architects, right?
They're always so busy.

24:18.624 --> 24:19.790
Yeah.

24:19.942 --> 24:22.351
[all agreeing]

24:22.369 --> 24:23.794
Um, that call's probably
going to take a while.

24:24.021 --> 24:26.038
So, jordan,
you want to say grace?

24:26.132 --> 24:27.965
Okay.

24:28.116 --> 24:31.376
[breathing heavily]

24:31.529 --> 24:33.971
[jordan praying indistinctly]

24:38.293 --> 24:39.702
I can't do this.

24:39.720 --> 24:40.811
All right.

24:47.211 --> 24:49.636
-Jordan: ...And somebody in.
-[phone buzzing]

24:49.655 --> 24:52.898
Blessing them to have
the ability to make this food,

24:53.050 --> 24:55.326
Lord, please bless the hands.

24:55.553 --> 24:59.163
[sighing]

25:01.242 --> 25:05.652
Thank you for working
and providing

25:05.671 --> 25:08.255
And blessings...
[continues indistinctly]

25:13.846 --> 25:16.680
♪♪

25:25.750 --> 25:28.083
What's up? How they treatin' you
out there today?

25:28.102 --> 25:31.253
[loretta humming]

25:31.346 --> 25:33.422
Loretta brown, there she is.

25:33.515 --> 25:35.924
Marcel leray, is that you?

25:35.943 --> 25:38.260
It's me. I read so much
about this place,

25:38.279 --> 25:40.596
I thought now that I'm here,
I should give it a visit.

25:40.614 --> 25:42.431
Come and give me a hug.

25:42.524 --> 25:45.042
-It's been years.
-Yes.

25:45.193 --> 25:46.769
Chris, could you
make him a plate?

25:46.862 --> 25:47.861
-Yes, ma'am.
-Thank you.

25:47.880 --> 25:49.529
Let's catch up.

25:49.623 --> 25:51.865
-I'd like that.
-Okay.

25:51.959 --> 25:54.793
I've been getting a little
lonesome since I've been here.

25:54.945 --> 25:57.629
Figured I should reconnect
with the people I grew up with.

25:57.723 --> 26:01.784
Haven't been able
to find many of the old gang.

26:01.802 --> 26:03.043
I mean, probably wouldn't
recognize me now anyway.

26:03.137 --> 26:05.971
I recognized you, didn't I?

26:06.123 --> 26:09.124
Well, because you
have an eye for beauty.

26:09.217 --> 26:12.294
Oh, maybe the faces change,

26:12.313 --> 26:14.554
But you're still
one arrogant old man.

26:14.574 --> 26:18.984
You know, if I recall,
I also had an eye for beauty.

26:19.136 --> 26:23.822
[chuckles] so tell me, what are
your plans for christmas?

26:23.916 --> 26:27.159
Well, I'll probably buy a big,
old roast beef po' boy

26:27.253 --> 26:28.752
And watch a game.

26:28.979 --> 26:31.146
That's no way
to spend christmas.

26:31.165 --> 26:33.498
My family's having
a big party on the 23rd.

26:33.593 --> 26:35.241
You should come.

26:35.261 --> 26:37.319
Pass a good time
with some good people.

26:37.412 --> 26:40.246
-I would be honored.
-Good.

26:40.266 --> 26:43.325
-Then, it's a date.
-A date?

26:43.418 --> 26:44.768
Don't get it twisted, honey.

26:44.995 --> 26:47.587
I'm a little rusty,
but yes, a date.

26:47.607 --> 26:50.256
-I have one question.
-Mm-hm.

26:50.276 --> 26:52.109
Will there be
any gumbo at this party?

26:52.336 --> 26:54.186
I have been
craving me some gumbo.

26:54.280 --> 26:56.004
Oh, there will be gumbo.

26:56.098 --> 26:58.006
Last night,
I started my test batch,

26:58.025 --> 27:00.025
And it's currently
sitting on my stove

27:00.119 --> 27:01.677
For taste testing.

27:01.695 --> 27:04.604
-That so?
-Mm-hm. It is.

27:04.624 --> 27:06.790
If you'd like, you can
come over and give it a try.

27:06.942 --> 27:08.684
Wait a minute.

27:08.702 --> 27:11.186
Are you inviting me
on our second date

27:11.279 --> 27:13.613
Before we have the first date?

27:13.633 --> 27:16.024
Let's take it one date
at a time, okay?

27:16.043 --> 27:17.635
-Okay.
-[mugs clinking]

27:20.381 --> 27:24.958
Okay. Miss loretta,
I'm just so sorry

27:24.977 --> 27:27.369
That I walked out
on lunch yesterday.

27:27.388 --> 27:29.462
And I just-- I just
have to explain that, um--

27:29.482 --> 27:30.648
Grace?

27:30.799 --> 27:32.799
Hey, anthony.

27:32.818 --> 27:34.634
-Hey.
-Hey.

27:34.728 --> 27:37.562
It is so good to see you.

27:37.715 --> 27:39.731
I wanted to apologize.

27:39.825 --> 27:41.975
I'm-- I'm sorry that
I left early yesterday.

27:41.994 --> 27:43.994
No, that's okay.

27:44.146 --> 27:47.647
Uncle anthony says
that you're a great architect,

27:47.741 --> 27:51.317
And sometimes great architects
have to take important calls.

27:51.337 --> 27:53.319
Oh, yes,
so I'm a great architect, huh?

27:53.339 --> 27:54.897
[laughs]

27:54.990 --> 27:56.899
Hey, jordan,
why don't you go ahead

27:56.917 --> 27:57.925
And go inside, okay?
Wait for me, all right?

28:01.347 --> 28:03.514
[door creaking]

28:03.665 --> 28:07.518
-We missed you yesterday.
-Yeah, I'm-- I'm sorry.

28:07.669 --> 28:10.670
You know, obviously I've--
I've said grace before,

28:10.690 --> 28:13.098
But everything
was just a little bit, um--

28:13.192 --> 28:14.583
Overwhelming?

28:14.601 --> 28:16.694
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

28:16.921 --> 28:20.589
I just-- I was just
so afraid to mess up.

28:20.682 --> 28:23.442
And I'm not really that good

28:23.594 --> 28:25.202
At being put on the spot.
It's hard for me.

28:25.353 --> 28:27.262
It's okay.

28:27.281 --> 28:29.522
You know,
my brother, christopher, he, uh,

28:29.616 --> 28:31.709
He's been trying to get
out of saying grace for years.

28:31.936 --> 28:33.877
He usually just
stumbles and mumbles along

28:34.029 --> 28:36.714
Until I say "amen"
to put him out of his misery.

28:36.865 --> 28:38.382
It's fine.

28:38.609 --> 28:42.127
Honestly, the truth
is that, um...

28:42.279 --> 28:44.871
I haven't gotten
to do this whole--

28:44.965 --> 28:46.965
Whole family thing since...

28:47.059 --> 28:49.468
Since I lost my parents.

28:49.562 --> 28:54.732
Being around your family
and all of this love, it...

28:54.959 --> 28:57.476
Made me realize
how much I missed my family.

28:57.570 --> 28:59.403
Yeah, I get it.

28:59.630 --> 29:01.296
My grandfather
died when I was ten.

29:01.389 --> 29:03.465
My parents split after that.

29:03.484 --> 29:06.243
My dad moved to atlanta,
and I just...

29:06.470 --> 29:08.579
[sighs]

29:08.730 --> 29:10.396
Well, I just think you
have to love who you got,

29:10.491 --> 29:11.990
While you got 'em.

29:12.142 --> 29:16.920
Mm. So, is that
why you work 24/7

29:17.147 --> 29:19.739
And don't make time
for your family?

29:19.759 --> 29:22.575
I mean, I'm just saying,
people do talk.

29:22.595 --> 29:24.428
I love my family
more than anything.

29:24.655 --> 29:26.505
They're the reason
I work so hard.

29:26.599 --> 29:29.508
Anthony, they don't care
about how much money you make

29:29.660 --> 29:31.417
Or how big
of a business you build.

29:31.437 --> 29:33.771
Wow. You know,
I came here for pralines

29:33.922 --> 29:36.014
And now I'm getting read.
-Okay.

29:36.108 --> 29:40.002
Well, I guess, we both
have something to learn, right?

29:40.020 --> 29:43.855
You want to come inside with me?
Grab a snack?

29:44.008 --> 29:45.507
-I'm not intruding--
-no.

29:45.600 --> 29:46.617
Are you okay
with me tagging along?

29:46.768 --> 29:49.027
Yeah. Yeah.

29:49.179 --> 29:52.180
You know, in fact... I think
you might be able to help me.

29:52.199 --> 29:53.624
With what?

30:03.694 --> 30:04.617
Grace: Are you sure
this is a good idea?

30:04.637 --> 30:06.286
I need
my grandma's secret recipe.

30:06.305 --> 30:08.121
But why?

30:09.141 --> 30:11.533
I have something to prove,
and I never lose a bet.

30:11.626 --> 30:13.218
Once I
get this place updated,

30:13.370 --> 30:14.770
Loretta's will be
a household name.

30:16.649 --> 30:19.391
-Why are you not standing watch?
-I see her out there

30:19.543 --> 30:20.800
Having coffee with someone.
Don't worry.

30:20.894 --> 30:22.727
It's just a praline recipe.

30:22.822 --> 30:24.546
Just a praline recipe.

30:24.639 --> 30:26.573
You are clearly
not from around here.

30:29.403 --> 30:30.569
[safe clicking]

30:30.663 --> 30:32.329
-Oh!
-Oh, you did it.

30:33.891 --> 30:35.574
Yeah.

30:35.668 --> 30:37.668
-[laughs]
-what?

30:37.819 --> 30:40.653
All right,
now feast your eyes on this.

30:40.673 --> 30:44.424
-[popping]
-[grace laughing]

30:45.919 --> 30:48.328
Look at the note! [laughs]

30:48.347 --> 30:50.589
You think
that's funny, don't you?

30:50.683 --> 30:52.516
Oh, it's funny. [laughs]

30:52.743 --> 30:54.334
Did you think your mama
wasn't going to tell me

30:54.428 --> 30:55.686
About your little praline plan?

30:55.837 --> 30:57.429
Hey, grandma.

30:57.581 --> 30:59.081
Don't you "grandma" me.

30:59.099 --> 31:01.191
If you want to
modernize this place,

31:01.418 --> 31:04.252
You have to figure
that out all on your own.

31:04.346 --> 31:06.088
Grandma, I've been trying,
it's just--

31:06.181 --> 31:08.181
-Can you give me a hint?
-[laughs] a hint.

31:08.200 --> 31:10.609
I'm a manager here.
She ain't give me a hint yet.

31:10.761 --> 31:13.036
You want a hint?
Take a hint and get out of here.

31:13.188 --> 31:15.780
-Oh.
-Okay.

31:15.875 --> 31:17.207
-Come on. Let's go.
-Okay.

31:17.434 --> 31:19.117
Let's go.

31:19.211 --> 31:20.952
I know when I'm beat.

31:21.105 --> 31:23.714
Mm-mm-mm.

31:23.941 --> 31:27.792
-Um, hi, miss, loretta.
-Yes, honey?

31:27.945 --> 31:29.535
I'm really
sorry about yesterday.

31:29.555 --> 31:31.463
There's nothing to be sorry for.

31:31.615 --> 31:35.300
No, no. I-- I shouldn't have
run out the way that I did.

31:35.394 --> 31:38.286
Honey, when I met you,

31:38.380 --> 31:39.804
I could see
something in your eyes

31:39.899 --> 31:41.714
I used to see in my own.

31:41.734 --> 31:45.127
-What's that?
-Loneliness.

31:45.220 --> 31:49.055
When I lost my husband,
anthony's grandfather,

31:49.149 --> 31:51.199
I felt it, too.

31:52.636 --> 31:55.561
But having my family
helped me get through it.

31:55.581 --> 31:59.157
So, if you ever want
a little bit of family

31:59.309 --> 32:01.919
And if you're ever
ready to open your heart

32:02.146 --> 32:04.813
And let some other
people love you again,

32:04.906 --> 32:08.216
Just know that
this door is always open.

32:12.414 --> 32:14.656
-Thank you.
-No problem, baby.

32:14.749 --> 32:17.267
So, have you had
a tour of the city yet?

32:18.938 --> 32:20.938
Not yet.

32:21.165 --> 32:23.089
Because I happen to
know a fabulous tour guide.

32:23.108 --> 32:24.424
[loretta giggling]

32:24.443 --> 32:25.758
I'm sure you do.

32:25.778 --> 32:27.736
[grace laughing]

32:33.786 --> 32:36.011
Anthony: Another thing to notice
as we move through the city

32:36.029 --> 32:37.955
Is that much of the architecture
you're seeing isn't even french.

32:38.182 --> 32:40.182
Oh.

32:40.200 --> 32:41.625
You know, french quarter
is kind of a misnomer

32:41.776 --> 32:43.776
Because most of the city--

32:43.870 --> 32:46.204
Burned down and was rebuilt
by the spanish colonists.

32:46.298 --> 32:48.023
Okay, listen, anthony,

32:48.116 --> 32:52.135
I know all
of textbook new orleans.

32:52.287 --> 32:54.620
Why don't you show me
your new orleans?

32:54.715 --> 32:55.472
My new orleans?

32:58.702 --> 33:00.477
-Okay, let's go.
-Okay.

33:02.055 --> 33:06.391
[festive jazz music playing]

33:06.485 --> 33:08.652
Where are you taking me?

33:08.879 --> 33:11.488
You'll see.

33:11.715 --> 33:15.884
Oh, my goodness,
this is beautiful.

33:15.977 --> 33:20.071
Anthony! Oh, what are
you doing here?

33:20.224 --> 33:23.074
I thought you were too busy
with work to come by today?

33:23.227 --> 33:24.726
-Hi.
-Oh, we're working.

33:24.745 --> 33:26.503
Yeah, we're just
doing some city research

33:26.730 --> 33:28.246
Getting ready to draft plans
for grandma's house.

33:28.398 --> 33:30.656
Now, if you really
want to learn your way

33:30.751 --> 33:31.991
Around the city,
there's no better way

33:32.085 --> 33:33.510
Than the jingle bell hop.

33:33.661 --> 33:35.328
-Jingle bell hop?
-It's nothing.

33:35.347 --> 33:37.014
It's only the best way

33:37.165 --> 33:38.831
To experience
new orleans at christmas.

33:38.925 --> 33:41.667
But you have to go by teams.

33:41.687 --> 33:44.746
Well, I mean, if it's
the best way to see the city...

33:44.765 --> 33:46.523
Mm-hmm.

33:46.674 --> 33:49.175
Yeah, grandma
put you up to this?

33:49.194 --> 33:51.528
No, you know, I'm helpless
against your grandmother.

33:51.755 --> 33:52.863
[laughs]

33:53.014 --> 33:54.197
Come on,
let's get you two signed up.

33:59.112 --> 34:01.687
[amplified voice] all right,
everyone, welcome, welcome.

34:01.707 --> 34:04.766
Thank you so much for
coming for the jingle bell hop.

34:04.859 --> 34:06.209
-Yeah. [laughs]
-[cheers and applause]

34:06.436 --> 34:08.103
Whoo!

34:08.121 --> 34:10.455
Let me tell you about the rules.
They're pretty simple.

34:10.607 --> 34:12.549
All around downtown,

34:12.700 --> 34:15.627
Locations are marked
with a jingle bell hop wreath.

34:15.721 --> 34:17.554
[laughs]

34:17.781 --> 34:20.223
And at each location,
there is a challenge.

34:20.375 --> 34:25.287
And if you succeed in
that challenge, you win a bell!

34:25.305 --> 34:26.897
[tina giggling]

34:27.048 --> 34:28.899
And the first team
that returns here

34:29.050 --> 34:30.883
With the most bells, wins.

34:30.903 --> 34:33.737
Okay, so what exactly
does the winner get?

34:34.981 --> 34:36.965
Only the best prize of all.

34:36.983 --> 34:38.967
-Hm?
-Bragging rights.

34:39.060 --> 34:41.244
All right, everyone,
on your marks.

34:41.471 --> 34:42.895
Get set.

34:42.989 --> 34:44.989
[plays fanfare]

34:45.142 --> 34:47.659
♪♪

34:47.753 --> 34:49.920
[laughs] yay!

34:50.071 --> 34:52.330
Oh, my goodness,

34:52.424 --> 34:55.074
The detail on these
buildings is incredible.

34:55.094 --> 34:56.576
-Yeah, some other time.
-What?

34:56.670 --> 34:57.986
You were talking about work?

34:58.004 --> 35:00.746
What? [squeals]

35:00.841 --> 35:02.824
I got the pearl,
I got the pearl.

35:02.843 --> 35:04.250
We got the pearl.

35:04.344 --> 35:05.936
-Yeah!
-[cheers and applause]

35:06.163 --> 35:10.440
♪♪

35:18.175 --> 35:20.024
Yay!

35:20.119 --> 35:22.844
Whoa!

35:22.937 --> 35:25.789
[laughter]

35:28.627 --> 35:32.254
♪♪

35:35.375 --> 35:37.801
I found it! I found it!

35:37.952 --> 35:40.545
You know, I still remember
the day you screamed

35:40.639 --> 35:42.788
Because you thought this
little lizard was an alligator.

35:42.883 --> 35:45.550
Oh, you weren't any better.

35:45.702 --> 35:47.552
That was the day
your hair started turning white.

35:47.646 --> 35:49.813
Oh. [chuckles]

35:49.964 --> 35:51.648
We had some good times
back in the day, didn't we?

35:51.875 --> 35:53.375
Yeah.

35:53.468 --> 35:54.559
And the good times
aren't over yet.

35:54.653 --> 35:56.486
You're right.

35:57.656 --> 35:59.823
I'm going to
a christmas pageant today.

35:59.974 --> 36:01.474
Would you like to join me?

36:01.568 --> 36:03.493
Well, let me check my calendar.

36:03.720 --> 36:05.720
Baby, you know
you don't have no calendar.

36:05.739 --> 36:07.330
-Hush up and try this.
-Okay.

36:11.061 --> 36:12.744
Mmm!

36:12.838 --> 36:14.579
You weren't wrong.

36:14.673 --> 36:16.731
This is some of the best
gumbo I've ever had.

36:16.824 --> 36:18.733
Mm-hmm.
Well, I know it's good gumbo.

36:18.752 --> 36:21.569
But don't you go
falling in love with me.

36:21.663 --> 36:23.138
We haven't had
our first date yet.

36:24.758 --> 36:26.349
Well, let's get
this party started.

36:28.187 --> 36:30.312
Okay.

36:34.100 --> 36:37.843
Oh, all right, you guys,
you're the first ones to arrive.

36:37.863 --> 36:41.940
Oh, wait, in order to win
the final and most coveted bell,

36:42.034 --> 36:45.427
You must find the beautiful
fleur de lis on this tree.

36:45.445 --> 36:46.928
That's going to
be like a hundred--

36:46.947 --> 36:48.872
Well, 304, to be exact.

36:49.099 --> 36:50.690
One for every year
since new orleans was founded.

36:50.709 --> 36:52.876
-Go, go, go. Get going.
-Okay.

36:53.103 --> 36:54.544
You know,
others can't be far behind you.

36:54.696 --> 36:55.954
I'll take this one.
This one here.

36:56.106 --> 36:57.547
This one?

36:59.367 --> 37:00.942
Oh, my goodness,
this is the most fun

37:00.961 --> 37:02.460
That I have had
in such a long time.

37:02.554 --> 37:03.887
♪♪

37:06.225 --> 37:08.541
What, what, what? Oh!

37:08.635 --> 37:10.710
I can't reach it.

37:10.804 --> 37:11.970
Oh, okay,
hang on, hang on, I got you.

37:12.122 --> 37:13.455
Ooh!

37:13.473 --> 37:15.807
[both laughing]

37:15.901 --> 37:18.818
Um...

37:20.630 --> 37:23.965
We found it! We found it!

37:23.984 --> 37:25.967
[laughs]
ladies and gentlemen,

37:26.060 --> 37:28.820
With all
of the bells and the final one.

37:28.972 --> 37:31.331
The winners this year
are grace and anthony.

37:33.159 --> 37:34.142
-[cheers and applause]
-yes!

37:34.235 --> 37:36.644
Thank you!

37:36.663 --> 37:40.331
Good job, son. [laughs]

37:40.484 --> 37:44.243
Yeah. So, you said
this was the most fun

37:44.337 --> 37:46.654
You've had in a long time.

37:46.748 --> 37:48.080
Don't let it go to your head.

37:48.100 --> 37:49.432
-Too late.
-[laughs]

37:49.659 --> 37:51.009
[laughs]

37:51.161 --> 37:52.251
-So...
-So, uh...

37:52.271 --> 37:55.272
[bell tolling]

37:55.423 --> 37:57.423
-Oh, is it that time?
-What? What time?

37:57.442 --> 37:59.609
I, uh... [sighs]

37:59.836 --> 38:01.352
I told jordan I'd go
to her christmas pageant.

38:01.505 --> 38:03.262
Oh.

38:03.356 --> 38:05.507
-Would you want to come with me?
-Yeah.

38:05.525 --> 38:07.767
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

38:07.786 --> 38:09.286
I mean, we got to show
our bells off somewhere, right?

38:09.513 --> 38:11.103
Yes, we do.

38:11.123 --> 38:12.363
-[grace giggling]
-okay, let's go.

38:12.457 --> 38:13.456
Okay, I'll follow you.

38:20.114 --> 38:23.858
[indistinct conversations]

38:23.951 --> 38:25.360
Anthony, you okay?
[laughs]

38:25.453 --> 38:27.545
-Yeah, why?
-You look nervous.

38:27.639 --> 38:30.031
Dancing and prancing like
one of santa's reindeer.

38:30.050 --> 38:32.216
So, you got jokes tonight.

38:32.311 --> 38:34.960
Well, I could talk about
your bad design aesthetic

38:34.980 --> 38:36.479
If you want me to.

38:36.631 --> 38:38.890
Please don't.
You're reminding me

38:39.042 --> 38:40.966
I got to get back
and work on that redesign.

38:40.986 --> 38:42.727
Tonight is about jordan.

38:42.821 --> 38:46.230
She's going to be
so happy that you are here.

38:46.383 --> 38:48.049
-I hope so.
-[laughs]

38:48.068 --> 38:49.826
[both laughing]

38:50.053 --> 38:52.978
Is that my grandma?
Who is she with?

38:53.073 --> 38:57.500
I don't know, but he is handsome
and she is looking very happy.

38:57.652 --> 38:59.410
-Unbelievable.
-[laughs]

38:59.563 --> 39:01.338
It's only been a day,
she's already got a man.

39:01.489 --> 39:04.841
Listen, be nice, okay?

39:04.992 --> 39:06.584
And I'm going to go get
in the hot cocoa line.

39:06.678 --> 39:08.753
You want some?

39:08.847 --> 39:09.921
I think I'll need
something stronger than cocoa.

39:10.073 --> 39:10.847
I'll see what I can do.

39:13.760 --> 39:14.851
Oh, thanks.

39:15.002 --> 39:19.097
[indistinct conversations]

39:19.191 --> 39:21.483
-Hey.
-Hi.

39:24.087 --> 39:26.588
Pick up, pick up,
pick up, pick up.

39:26.606 --> 39:28.198
[phone ringing]

39:31.352 --> 39:33.277
Hey, grace, what's up?

39:33.372 --> 39:37.690
Hey, um, did I catch you
at a bad time? Can you talk?

39:37.784 --> 39:39.267
<i> Are you all right?</i>

39:39.360 --> 39:40.952
Yes, I'm at a christmas pageant.

39:41.046 --> 39:42.379
<i> With anthony?</i>

39:42.606 --> 39:45.790
Uh, sounds romantic.
Dish, please.

39:45.942 --> 39:48.776
No, no, no, no.
There is nothing to dish.

39:48.795 --> 39:51.279
Right. Lots of architectural
drafting to be done

39:51.372 --> 39:53.223
At a christmas pageant,
I'm sure.

39:53.450 --> 39:55.392
Okay, just-- just--
just listen, please.

39:55.543 --> 39:59.454
So yesterday,
I completely embarrassed myself

39:59.547 --> 40:01.064
In front of his whole family.

40:01.215 --> 40:03.233
We're still not seeing
eye to eye on this project,

40:03.384 --> 40:05.718
And for some reason,
everyone is being so nice to me.

40:05.737 --> 40:08.387
I don't know. It's just--
it's just this weird feeling,

40:08.407 --> 40:10.389
Like I might
actually belong here.

40:10.483 --> 40:12.800
<i> And that can't happen</i>

40:12.819 --> 40:14.969
<i> Because I'm so close</i>
<i> to getting this toronto job,</i>

40:14.988 --> 40:17.805
And I haven't felt
like this in so long.

40:17.899 --> 40:21.233
Well, first of all, enjoy it.

40:21.327 --> 40:24.312
Second of all, you never
know what everyone is thinking.

40:24.330 --> 40:25.588
I remember--

40:25.740 --> 40:27.406
Alexis, hold on one sec.

40:27.426 --> 40:29.317
Actually, let me
give you a call back, okay?

40:29.335 --> 40:31.094
But don't you wanna
hear the rest of my speech?

40:31.321 --> 40:32.762
I'll call you later.
All right, bye.

40:36.993 --> 40:37.934
Oh.

40:40.513 --> 40:42.105
I give great advice.

40:46.352 --> 40:49.946
[indistinct conversations]

40:54.027 --> 40:58.621
Hey. I heard you back here

40:58.848 --> 40:59.289
And thought
I'd come wish you luck.

40:59.440 --> 41:01.532
What's going on?

41:01.626 --> 41:05.628
Did they send you back here
to try to make me go up there?

41:05.855 --> 41:08.781
No, but why
don't you want to sing?

41:08.875 --> 41:11.025
Can I tell you something?

41:11.044 --> 41:14.971
And you promise you
won't tell any other grown-ups?

41:15.122 --> 41:16.639
I promise.

41:16.791 --> 41:18.308
Pinky promise.

41:20.127 --> 41:22.395
There's a lot
of people out there.

41:23.631 --> 41:25.890
I just wish mom
was here to sing, too.

41:26.042 --> 41:27.984
Can you keep a secret for me?

41:29.303 --> 41:30.987
I completely understand.

41:32.398 --> 41:34.807
Because I feel the same way.

41:34.826 --> 41:37.719
-Really?
-Mm-hm.

41:37.737 --> 41:43.649
Do you know what makes you
so incredibly special?

41:43.668 --> 41:45.226
What?

41:45.319 --> 41:47.078
Even though your mom isn't here,

41:47.230 --> 41:52.233
You have
a whole family of people

41:52.252 --> 41:54.660
Who are out in the audience

41:54.679 --> 41:58.163
Waiting to cheer you on
and loves you.

41:58.183 --> 42:00.350
You know what? They don't care
if you forget the words

42:00.501 --> 42:02.076
Or if your voice cracks.

42:02.169 --> 42:04.245
None of that matters to them.

42:04.264 --> 42:06.505
Come on, I'll walk you out.

42:06.599 --> 42:08.766
Oh, you've got this.

42:08.918 --> 42:13.196
You got this, you hear me?
[laughs]

42:13.347 --> 42:17.534
[indistinct conversations]

42:17.685 --> 42:20.595
[bells jingling]

42:20.613 --> 42:22.205
So, where's your colleague?

42:24.267 --> 42:25.524
Shouldn't you be
worried about your boyfriend?

42:25.618 --> 42:27.118
He is not my boyfriend.

42:27.270 --> 42:28.878
Not yet.

42:30.215 --> 42:32.290
Whoo! [laughs]

42:32.442 --> 42:34.384
-[audience cheering]
-ladies and gentlemen.

42:34.535 --> 42:37.703
Welcome, everybody,
to our annual christmas pageant.

42:37.797 --> 42:41.206
I know you're excited
to get into the holiday spirit,

42:41.226 --> 42:43.618
So I will go ahead

42:43.636 --> 42:47.730
And introduce our first number
sung by jordan brown!

42:47.882 --> 42:52.026
[cheers and applause]

43:01.638 --> 43:06.416
[piano plays intro]

43:08.402 --> 43:12.163
[audience murmuring]

43:12.257 --> 43:18.428
[piano replays intro]

43:18.579 --> 43:23.749
[audience murmuring]

43:23.768 --> 43:25.226
[whispers] go.

43:28.681 --> 43:30.014
[lowered voice] me?

43:30.166 --> 43:31.608
Please?

43:35.672 --> 43:36.613
Okay.

43:43.029 --> 43:47.624
[audience murmuring]

43:47.851 --> 43:49.792
[whispering]
I don't have the words.

43:49.944 --> 43:51.252
It's okay.

43:53.632 --> 43:54.964
Let's do this.

43:57.302 --> 44:01.804
[piano restarts intro]

44:03.624 --> 44:07.535
<i>♪ hark, the herald angels sing ♪</i>

44:07.628 --> 44:11.814
<i> ♪ glory to the newborn king ♪</i>

44:12.041 --> 44:16.711
<i> ♪ peace on earth</i>
<i> and mercy mild ♪</i>

44:16.804 --> 44:21.215
<i> ♪ god and sinners reconciled ♪</i>

44:21.308 --> 44:25.161
<i>♪ joyful, all ye nations, rise ♪</i>

44:25.388 --> 44:29.815
<i> ♪ join the triumph</i>
<i> of the skies ♪</i>

44:29.834 --> 44:34.061
<i> ♪ with angelic host proclaim ♪</i>

44:34.155 --> 44:38.399
<i>♪ christ is born in bethlehem ♪</i>

44:38.492 --> 44:41.903
<i>♪ hark, the herald angels sing ♪</i>

44:41.996 --> 44:47.758
<i> ♪ glory to the newborn king ♪</i>

44:47.852 --> 44:49.852
♪♪

44:50.004 --> 44:53.022
[cheers and applause]

45:01.533 --> 45:04.867
All right, I think I figured out
grandma's recipe.

45:05.094 --> 45:08.095
These are the best ones
right here.

45:08.114 --> 45:10.948
Uh, are you sure?

45:11.100 --> 45:13.025
Because, listen, I'm still full

45:13.044 --> 45:14.785
From your grandmother's
jambalaya.

45:14.879 --> 45:17.104
-I can really sit this one out--
-grace, stop making excuses.

45:17.123 --> 45:19.531
-[groans]
-eat the praline.

45:19.625 --> 45:20.791
-[sighs]
-ready?

45:20.885 --> 45:23.720
Three, two...

45:26.466 --> 45:29.225
[munching loudly]

45:29.376 --> 45:33.955
Mm-mm, mm-mm, mm-mm.
That is awful.

45:33.973 --> 45:37.066
Oh my goodness, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, but it is--

45:37.293 --> 45:38.901
The worst thing
I ever tasted in my life.

45:39.053 --> 45:40.461
I don't know
what I'm doing wrong.

45:40.480 --> 45:42.463
I mean, what are pralines?

45:42.556 --> 45:43.798
They're sugar, they're butter,
they're--

45:43.891 --> 45:46.467
Apparently, burnt pecans.
[laughs]

45:46.486 --> 45:48.578
-Funny.
-Well, listen,

45:48.805 --> 45:50.562
Let's look
at the bright side, okay?

45:50.582 --> 45:52.915
At least
you decided to be an architect,

45:53.067 --> 45:54.584
And not a candy maker.

45:54.811 --> 45:56.994
-[sarcastically] ha-ha-ha.
-Ha-ha-ha.

45:57.088 --> 45:59.088
Speaking of which,
let's see what you got here.

46:05.171 --> 46:08.489
-Wait, grace.
-Yes.

46:08.508 --> 46:10.582
What did you do with
my beautiful house design?

46:10.676 --> 46:12.994
Okay, look, you are not
going to put concrete finishes

46:13.012 --> 46:15.346
In this house.
I'm not going to allow it.

46:15.498 --> 46:16.847
I don't know.
You're impossible.

46:16.941 --> 46:21.669
Anthony, your grandmother
is a new orleans icon,

46:21.687 --> 46:25.114
And we have to give her
an iconic new orleans home.

46:25.266 --> 46:26.949
Yeah, but this new orleans
is the 21st century,

46:27.101 --> 46:28.618
Not the dark ages.

46:28.769 --> 46:30.269
New orleans
is a melting pot, right?

46:30.288 --> 46:32.696
-Yeah.
-Exactly.

46:32.849 --> 46:35.774
And we have to give
your grandmother a home

46:35.868 --> 46:38.035
That reflects that melting pot.

46:38.129 --> 46:40.538
A little bit of french,
a little bit of haitian.

46:40.632 --> 46:44.616
The warmth of reclaimed wood
with modern metal.

46:44.710 --> 46:46.636
It's classic meets modern.

46:48.122 --> 46:49.806
-That could work.
-Good.

46:50.033 --> 46:52.366
Because when I talked
to your grandmother,

46:52.385 --> 46:57.538
She said her dream was
to have a house that generations

46:57.557 --> 47:00.132
Could come and spend christmas.

47:00.226 --> 47:02.560
And we can give her that.

47:02.712 --> 47:04.395
Okay, well, what about you?

47:04.489 --> 47:06.714
-Me?
-Yeah.

47:06.732 --> 47:08.307
What about your christmas?

47:08.401 --> 47:10.809
-My christmas?
-Yeah.

47:10.903 --> 47:12.053
Like, we spend so much time
talking about me and my family,

47:12.071 --> 47:14.555
Our traditions.

47:14.648 --> 47:16.574
But you have some
traditions, I'm sure.

47:16.726 --> 47:18.392
Okay, yeah, we're not
here to talk about me.

47:18.411 --> 47:20.561
We're doing this project
for your family,

47:20.580 --> 47:21.896
So let's get back to work.

47:21.989 --> 47:24.173
Grace, you can share. It's okay.

47:26.177 --> 47:29.846
Okay, either you start talking,
or you start eating.

47:29.997 --> 47:31.347
Okay, anything but that.

47:31.498 --> 47:35.076
They're not that bad.

47:35.094 --> 47:38.913
Fine. When I was a little girl,

47:39.006 --> 47:41.415
Me and my parents,
we would go outside,

47:41.508 --> 47:43.767
And we would make snow angels.

47:43.862 --> 47:49.514
And, um, I know it sounds
so silly, but to this day,

47:49.534 --> 47:52.684
When I'm really missing them,

47:52.778 --> 47:54.704
That's exactly what I do.

47:54.931 --> 47:56.539
I go outside
and make snow angels,

47:56.766 --> 48:00.376
And it instantly
feels like christmas.

48:01.880 --> 48:06.674
I know it's impossible
here in new orleans, but, um...

48:09.053 --> 48:12.388
I would give anything...

48:13.799 --> 48:16.225
To make snow angels with them
one more time.

48:16.377 --> 48:20.212
Well, hey, it is
the city of new orleans, right?

48:20.306 --> 48:22.381
Anything's possible.

48:22.475 --> 48:24.692
-Even snow?
-Maybe.

48:26.312 --> 48:29.463
Let's get back to work.

48:29.482 --> 48:32.633
All right. Now show me
what you're thinking.

48:32.652 --> 48:34.969
[jazz rendition of "hark
the herald angels sing" playing]

48:34.987 --> 48:36.579
[anthony sighing]

48:41.327 --> 48:43.494
I gotta get this.

48:43.588 --> 48:47.256
♪♪

49:05.851 --> 49:07.777
[muffled laughing]

49:10.782 --> 49:12.573
Here we go. [chuckles]

49:18.364 --> 49:19.622
Mmm.

49:20.516 --> 49:24.702
Mm-hmm. Hmm. Mm-mm.
[laughs]

49:24.796 --> 49:30.615
Mm. Mm. Mm-hmm.

49:30.710 --> 49:34.028
I don't know what went wrong.
The-- the recipe online said--

49:34.046 --> 49:37.715
Online? [scoffs]
well, that's your problem.

49:37.867 --> 49:40.125
Miss loretta's recipe
is five generations old.

49:40.144 --> 49:42.203
I had to start
from somewhere, ma.

49:42.221 --> 49:43.721
I definitely wouldn't
give that to your girlfriend.

49:43.873 --> 49:45.389
-Mm-mm.
-She's not my girlfriend.

49:45.483 --> 49:48.133
[laughs] that's not what
christopher's saying.

49:48.152 --> 49:49.560
Well, she won't
be your girlfriend,

49:49.712 --> 49:50.878
Not with that attitude.

49:50.971 --> 49:54.064
-Okay, who sent these?
-Anthony.

49:54.158 --> 49:56.884
I thought we talked
about you opening yourself up.

49:56.902 --> 49:59.996
I tried to.
But just hanging around her,

50:00.223 --> 50:01.555
It brings up
these feelings that--

50:01.574 --> 50:03.332
Feelings?

50:03.559 --> 50:08.078
Feelings.
Mm. Like what, son? [laughs]

50:08.172 --> 50:10.748
Weren't we talking about
grandma and her flowers?

50:10.900 --> 50:12.657
Your mother's not
going to fall for that, boo.

50:12.677 --> 50:15.085
[laughs]

50:15.179 --> 50:16.920
Did marcel send these?

50:17.073 --> 50:19.498
As a matter of fact, he did.

50:19.517 --> 50:21.091
Not that that's
any of your business.

50:21.244 --> 50:25.746
[chuckles] we're talking
about anthony and grace.

50:25.765 --> 50:28.582
Oh.

50:28.675 --> 50:30.417
Probably wouldn't work anyway.

50:30.436 --> 50:31.527
She says
new orleans is growing on her,

50:31.678 --> 50:33.921
But she's always moving.

50:33.939 --> 50:36.106
Then you need
to give her a reason to stay.

50:36.259 --> 50:38.701
-A reason to stay?
-Mm-hmm.

50:38.852 --> 50:43.097
You have to show people
how you feel, anthony.

50:43.190 --> 50:47.043
You tell us all the time
that you love us,

50:47.194 --> 50:49.879
But when was the last time
you actually spent time with us?

50:50.106 --> 50:52.940
[sighs] what she's trying
to say, son,

50:52.958 --> 50:55.885
Is that if you'd like her

50:56.036 --> 50:58.220
To feel like she belongs here,
like she could stay,

50:58.372 --> 51:00.205
Then you need
to prove it to her.

51:00.224 --> 51:03.893
Exactly. And please
don't go baking your feelings,

51:04.120 --> 51:05.061
Because we all know
you can't cook.

51:05.212 --> 51:07.712
[women laughing]

51:07.807 --> 51:09.881
No. Uh-uh. [laughs]

51:09.901 --> 51:12.309
Ooh. Mm.

51:12.461 --> 51:13.718
Did you want
to try one of these?

51:13.813 --> 51:14.978
-Oh, no.
-I'm good.

51:15.073 --> 51:16.989
Mm-mm. [laughs]

51:20.970 --> 51:22.244
[soft jazz playing]

51:28.586 --> 51:30.753
[phone buzzes]

51:35.760 --> 51:40.346
♪♪

51:44.602 --> 51:47.494
Anthony:
There's a little step down.

51:47.513 --> 51:49.346
If I-- if you let me
run into something.

51:49.498 --> 51:51.849
Okay, where are we going?

51:52.001 --> 51:54.168
-Just trust me.
-Please don't let me fall.

51:54.261 --> 51:56.019
-I got you.
-Oh, this feels shaky.

51:56.172 --> 51:57.596
Okay, one more step.

51:57.615 --> 52:00.841
-It's kind of a big one.
-Okay.

52:00.860 --> 52:02.676
Just one more after that,
just one more.

52:02.769 --> 52:04.511
-Oh, my goodness.
-Okay.

52:04.530 --> 52:06.622
-Okay, where are we going?
-Just walk further.

52:06.773 --> 52:08.124
-How much further?
-Almost there.

52:08.351 --> 52:10.367
How much?
Oh, wait, this feels weird.

52:10.519 --> 52:11.627
This is a change,
change, change?

52:11.854 --> 52:13.629
-Uh-huh.
-What's this under my feet?

52:13.856 --> 52:16.190
-What's happening?
-You're gonna sit right there.

52:16.208 --> 52:17.800
-What am I walking on?
-Okay. You're gonna find out--

52:18.027 --> 52:19.135
All right. No, no.
Right about...

52:20.880 --> 52:22.863
-Now.
-Oh! [laughs]

52:23.975 --> 52:28.035
I couldn't get a miracle,
but I could get you a whole

52:28.128 --> 52:30.295
Bunch of fake snow.
-How did you--

52:30.389 --> 52:32.055
Called in a few favors.

52:32.150 --> 52:33.315
Stuff was on
a mardi gras float last year.

52:36.045 --> 52:39.971
You did all of this,
all of this for me?

52:40.065 --> 52:45.219
Yeah. Grace, you said
you wanted to make snow angels.

52:45.312 --> 52:46.662
It's the least I could do.

52:50.334 --> 52:52.651
Come on, you got
to make one with me.

52:52.745 --> 52:54.561
-Let's go, let's go, let's go.
-Oh, this was for you.

52:54.580 --> 52:56.230
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.
Come on.

52:56.248 --> 52:58.232
-Okay.
-Okay, lay back.

52:58.250 --> 52:59.566
-All right.
-Lay back.

52:59.585 --> 53:01.735
[laughing]

53:01.754 --> 53:05.589
[giggling]

53:05.683 --> 53:08.926
Okay. I've never done this
before, so don't judge my form.

53:09.078 --> 53:10.835
Nobody's judging you.

53:10.855 --> 53:12.429
That's some
interesting form, though.

53:12.523 --> 53:14.023
[both laughing]

53:14.250 --> 53:16.525
[both sigh]

53:20.698 --> 53:23.590
[grunts]

53:23.609 --> 53:26.927
[both laugh]

53:26.946 --> 53:31.022
You know how you were saying,
um, you were starting to feel

53:31.042 --> 53:31.874
Like you wanted
to belong somewhere?

53:34.378 --> 53:37.046
Do you think
you could want to belong here,

53:37.197 --> 53:39.715
Like in new orleans?

53:39.866 --> 53:41.884
-Maybe.
-Yeah?

53:42.111 --> 53:45.721
I just-- I don't
know how to do that.

53:45.872 --> 53:47.281
Well, my grandma always
says that

53:47.299 --> 53:49.800
If you want to do anything,
you need--

53:49.952 --> 53:54.730
To practice. Yes, I heard.
[laughs]

53:54.957 --> 53:56.815
Um...

53:57.902 --> 53:58.901
You know,
I have a question for you.

53:59.128 --> 54:01.311
Shoot.

54:01.405 --> 54:03.981
Do you want to come
to this party with me?

54:04.075 --> 54:05.557
Really?

54:05.576 --> 54:07.910
Yeah.

54:08.061 --> 54:10.971
I mean, it's not every day
that a guy makes it snow

54:10.990 --> 54:12.564
For you in new orleans.

54:12.583 --> 54:14.416
[laughs]

54:16.645 --> 54:18.254
I'd love to.

54:18.481 --> 54:19.922
Good.

54:21.759 --> 54:24.318
Well, I do have one
last question for you.

54:24.336 --> 54:27.504
This is absolutely beautiful.
Um...

54:27.598 --> 54:29.765
Do you expect me
to help you clean all this up?

54:29.916 --> 54:31.842
Because if so, we probably
need to start now if we want

54:31.994 --> 54:33.769
To be done by new year's.

54:33.920 --> 54:36.330
No, I think we can
enjoy it a little bit longer.

54:36.348 --> 54:38.107
Perfect answer.

54:40.278 --> 54:43.094
♪♪

54:43.114 --> 54:47.098
<i> Hey, y'all, it's christmas!</i>
<i> Ha!</i>

54:47.192 --> 54:49.618
<i> -♪ I celebrate christmas ♪</i>
<i> -♪ christmas ♪</i>

54:49.845 --> 54:52.270
<i> ♪ it's the best time</i>
<i> of the year ♪</i>

54:52.290 --> 54:54.623
<i>♪ sure, there's just the cheer ♪</i>

54:54.775 --> 54:58.443
<i> ♪ everyone that celebrates</i>
<i> it's christmas ♪</i>

54:58.537 --> 54:59.461
<i> ♪ christmas ♪</i>

54:59.613 --> 55:01.872
<i> ♪ snow is falling down ♪</i>

55:02.024 --> 55:04.691
<i> ♪ santa's coming to town ♪</i>

55:04.785 --> 55:06.360
<i> ♪ everyone, let's celebrate ♪</i>

55:06.378 --> 55:08.787
<i> ♪ let's celebrate</i>
<i> the good times ♪</i>

55:08.806 --> 55:10.622
I know you're an introvert,
but are you ever going

55:10.641 --> 55:12.382
To leave the kitchen?
-I'm helping.

55:12.476 --> 55:15.978
-Is he here yet?
-Oh, honey, you need a drink.

55:16.129 --> 55:17.721
Maybe I shouldn't
have invited him.

55:17.873 --> 55:19.481
You really like him, don't you?

55:19.633 --> 55:21.800
I really do.

55:21.894 --> 55:24.135
Well, then come on.

55:24.229 --> 55:25.470
You want to be in the middle
of the action when he shows up.

55:25.489 --> 55:27.656
-Okay.
-Yeah.

55:29.160 --> 55:30.326
Thank you.

55:30.553 --> 55:32.494
I think people
like being outside.

55:32.646 --> 55:34.997
[murmuring]

55:37.409 --> 55:39.317
Looks like
your date finally got here.

55:39.337 --> 55:43.321
♪♪

55:43.415 --> 55:45.323
-Hey.
-Hey.

55:45.343 --> 55:47.659
Sorry, I'm late,
but I brought pralines.

55:47.678 --> 55:50.904
-Thanks, um...
-It's the tie, right?

55:50.923 --> 55:53.265
-Too much, isn't it?
-You look all right.

55:54.577 --> 55:57.427
Yes. He looks beautiful,
she looks beautiful.

55:57.580 --> 56:00.022
Hey, alexis. Oh, hey.

56:00.249 --> 56:01.840
You haven't changed
a bit since college.

56:01.859 --> 56:04.935
Oh, you are still a charmer,
and I love it.

56:05.087 --> 56:06.845
Now, come on. Join the party.

56:06.864 --> 56:09.531
-Let's get drinks!
-[laughs]

56:09.683 --> 56:12.275
All right now, be careful,
because she has rigged

56:12.428 --> 56:14.595
This whole party with mistletoe.

56:14.613 --> 56:18.281
We wouldn't want to, uh, fall
into one of her traps, would we?

56:18.434 --> 56:20.626
Yeah, we, uh, can't have that.

56:23.530 --> 56:25.547
Oh, yes, I'm glad you asked.

56:25.699 --> 56:28.384
Hey, everyone, I brought some
of my grandma's pralines.

56:28.535 --> 56:31.202
-Oh.
-[indistinct conversations]

56:31.222 --> 56:32.203
-Dig in.
-Mmm.

56:32.223 --> 56:34.114
Come on.

56:34.133 --> 56:36.541
Are you sure
they're miss loretta's?

56:36.560 --> 56:39.136
♪♪

56:39.230 --> 56:41.379
Did you tell her?

56:41.399 --> 56:42.956
-I didn't say anything.
-Sounds like you told her.

56:42.975 --> 56:44.733
I mean, the taste
isn't going to lie.

56:44.960 --> 56:45.976
Let me see.

56:46.128 --> 56:48.311
Mm.

56:48.406 --> 56:49.988
Looks like you're
going to have to keep trying.

56:53.911 --> 56:56.227
I'm just can't seem
to figure out what I'm missing.

56:56.321 --> 56:59.489
<i> ♪ holiday glow ♪</i>

56:59.642 --> 57:01.232
Attention, everyone!

57:01.326 --> 57:03.252
Come here, please.

57:04.329 --> 57:07.739
As the host of a multi-faith
melting pot holiday party,

57:07.758 --> 57:11.501
I obviously
appreciate all religions.

57:11.595 --> 57:15.338
So my office is having
a benefit where for every letter

57:15.433 --> 57:18.249
For santa they receive, they'll
be donating $1 to charity.

57:18.343 --> 57:19.826
-I have one.
-Oh.

57:19.845 --> 57:22.512
We have our first letter.
Thank you, grace.

57:22.606 --> 57:26.667
Before the night is over,
I want everyone here

57:26.760 --> 57:28.760
To write one letter to santa.

57:28.779 --> 57:30.112
And at the end of the night,
we'll pick the best one

57:30.263 --> 57:33.765
To be crowned king...
Or queen of the holidays.

57:33.859 --> 57:36.526
Make them funny.
Make them sweet.

57:36.679 --> 57:38.195
But don't make me cry.

57:38.289 --> 57:40.122
[laughter]

57:40.349 --> 57:42.440
-Okay.
-[indistinct conversations]

57:42.460 --> 57:45.185
You know, I almost forgot
alexis is, uh...

57:45.204 --> 57:47.129
The best?

57:47.356 --> 57:49.022
Yeah. This is why
you two get along so well.

57:49.041 --> 57:51.525
You know what? [laughs]

57:51.543 --> 57:54.452
You, sir,
need to write a letter to santa.

57:54.472 --> 57:56.138
Mm-hm.

58:02.371 --> 58:04.705
<i> ♪ christmas wish ♪</i>

58:04.723 --> 58:07.057
-I think that's enough, right?
-Yeah.

58:07.151 --> 58:08.375
Okay.

58:08.468 --> 58:09.651
I feel it!

58:09.803 --> 58:11.728
[shouting] yeah.

58:11.822 --> 58:13.155
[crowd cheering]

58:14.550 --> 58:17.743
♪♪

58:22.908 --> 58:24.833
[sighing]

58:26.837 --> 58:28.395
Come on, anthony, you've
been hiding this for years.

58:28.488 --> 58:31.840
Let's...
Just tell the truth.

58:34.661 --> 58:37.346
[indistinct conversations]

58:44.188 --> 58:46.096
-So, what you writing?
-Hey, hey, no cheating!

58:46.248 --> 58:48.765
There's no cheating
in letters to santa.

58:48.917 --> 58:52.435
It is when the prize is being
crowned king of the holidays.

58:52.530 --> 58:54.512
But don't you worry,
I'll be a fair and just ruler.

58:54.532 --> 58:56.089
Come on, let me see, let me see.

58:56.182 --> 58:58.200
You can't use
your height against me.

58:58.351 --> 59:00.277
All's fair
in love and war, grace.

59:00.371 --> 59:02.871
You'll see that once you
recognize me as christmas king.

59:03.098 --> 59:04.689
Well, what is this?

59:04.708 --> 59:06.959
Is it love or is it war?

59:09.104 --> 59:11.046
Can we go somewhere
and talk privately?

59:12.107 --> 59:14.532
Oh, is that a command
from the christmas king?

59:14.552 --> 59:17.010
How could I refuse?
Come on.

59:20.299 --> 59:23.892
What is this, um,
christmas emergency?

59:24.119 --> 59:25.394
[both laugh]

59:25.621 --> 59:27.187
Um...Well...

59:30.234 --> 59:32.067
I wanted you to read my letter
before anyone else did.

59:33.295 --> 59:35.645
What?
You giving me the advantage?

59:35.798 --> 59:37.573
That's not like you.

59:37.800 --> 59:40.967
Yeah, I'm not so good
with words sometimes,

59:41.061 --> 59:42.578
And I wanted
to get your feedback.

59:42.805 --> 59:44.746
You need to give
yourself more credit.

59:44.898 --> 59:50.085
You are a brilliant architect
and a good man,

59:50.312 --> 59:52.004
And a pretty good
bell hop partner.

59:55.150 --> 59:57.241
Okay. Ahem.

59:57.336 --> 59:58.719
[throat clearing]

1:00:00.264 --> 1:00:04.248
"dear santa, this might
sound like an unusual request,

1:00:04.268 --> 1:00:06.660
"but there's only one thing
on my list this year--

1:00:06.678 --> 1:00:09.754
One dream you could
help me make come true.

1:00:09.773 --> 1:00:13.183
I'd like for this one woman
to feel about me the way

1:00:13.277 --> 1:00:16.111
I felt about her since
the first moment I laid eyes

1:00:16.262 --> 1:00:19.005
On her all those years ago

1:00:19.024 --> 1:00:25.103
In dr. Carp's
freshman lectures. Um...

1:00:25.122 --> 1:00:28.348
The way I felt about her since

1:00:28.441 --> 1:00:30.792
She walked into my life
again a few days ago.

1:00:30.944 --> 1:00:33.629
All I want for christmas
this year is grace hill."

1:00:35.299 --> 1:00:38.300
Is this true?
Do you mean this?

1:00:38.527 --> 1:00:40.469
Every word.

1:00:40.620 --> 1:00:43.029
I wanted to tell you
back in college,

1:00:43.048 --> 1:00:44.640
But it was just
not the right time.

1:00:44.791 --> 1:00:47.392
I had feelings
for you too, back then.

1:00:49.054 --> 1:00:50.729
And I still do.

1:00:52.391 --> 1:00:53.649
Really?

1:00:53.800 --> 1:00:55.150
Yeah, and, uh...

1:00:57.303 --> 1:00:58.987
Looks like we're
under the mistletoe.

1:01:00.324 --> 1:01:02.324
-Good?
-Good.

1:01:02.993 --> 1:01:04.242
Great.

1:01:06.071 --> 1:01:08.813
[drums beating in distance]

1:01:08.832 --> 1:01:10.332
Is that a second line?

1:01:10.483 --> 1:01:12.501
[chuckles]

1:01:12.652 --> 1:01:14.244
-We've got to go. We should go.
-Okay, let's go.

1:01:14.396 --> 1:01:15.837
♪♪

1:01:15.989 --> 1:01:18.748
[cheering]

1:01:18.901 --> 1:01:21.843
♪♪

1:01:22.070 --> 1:01:24.254
[laughs]

1:01:24.348 --> 1:01:27.331
Okay. Remember when
I said the jingle bell hop

1:01:27.351 --> 1:01:29.184
Was the most fun I'd ever had?

1:01:29.411 --> 1:01:31.745
-Yeah.
-Yeah, that was back then.

1:01:31.838 --> 1:01:34.815
This is the most fun
I've ever had.

1:01:36.176 --> 1:01:38.009
Oh, good, because
it is only going to get better

1:01:38.103 --> 1:01:39.343
From here on out.

1:01:39.438 --> 1:01:41.771
-Really?
-Yeah.

1:01:41.924 --> 1:01:44.941
♪♪

1:01:45.035 --> 1:01:46.684
Come on!

1:01:46.704 --> 1:01:48.094
Okay!

1:01:48.188 --> 1:01:49.279
[laughter]

1:01:49.373 --> 1:01:54.543
♪♪

1:02:07.057 --> 1:02:09.115
[bell jingles]

1:02:09.209 --> 1:02:11.952
Sorry. We're getting ready
to close up.

1:02:12.045 --> 1:02:15.121
So early? I need
to get my praline fix on.

1:02:15.140 --> 1:02:17.048
Marcel!

1:02:17.142 --> 1:02:19.067
Now, you've been every day.

1:02:19.294 --> 1:02:21.052
There's no way that you've
gone through all those

1:02:21.071 --> 1:02:22.720
Pralines by yourself.

1:02:22.740 --> 1:02:24.464
Of course not.

1:02:24.557 --> 1:02:25.982
I've been giving
them away as gifts.

1:02:26.134 --> 1:02:28.076
-You must have a lot of friends.
-Well, you know,

1:02:28.303 --> 1:02:30.061
New neighbors. I'm trying to
make an impression.

1:02:30.155 --> 1:02:33.081
Mm, looking for your usual?

1:02:33.308 --> 1:02:35.399
Well, since you'll be
closed for christmas,

1:02:35.419 --> 1:02:36.734
We should double that.

1:02:36.754 --> 1:02:38.253
That'll just about clean me out.

1:02:38.404 --> 1:02:39.980
[chuckles]

1:02:39.998 --> 1:02:40.756
-There you go.
-I'll take it.

1:02:40.907 --> 1:02:41.882
Thank you.

1:02:43.819 --> 1:02:46.762
Marcel, what are
you really doing here?

1:02:46.913 --> 1:02:49.656
You can't have this many
neighbors. I know that.

1:02:49.674 --> 1:02:52.434
You could always
see right through me.

1:02:52.585 --> 1:02:54.677
You know, I--

1:02:54.830 --> 1:02:57.939
I like talking to you,
I like seeing you,

1:02:58.091 --> 1:02:59.924
So I've been
getting all these pralines

1:02:59.943 --> 1:03:04.112
And giving them out
to shelters for the holidays.

1:03:04.339 --> 1:03:07.857
I just use it as an excuse
to swing by and see you.

1:03:07.951 --> 1:03:10.268
You never need an excuse
to come and see me.

1:03:10.287 --> 1:03:11.286
Really? [laughs]

1:03:13.273 --> 1:03:15.849
I've been out of the game
so long I forgot how to play it.

1:03:15.867 --> 1:03:18.442
Well, we'll just have to
figure that out together then.

1:03:18.462 --> 1:03:20.444
But I do know where to start.

1:03:20.464 --> 1:03:21.963
Yeah?

1:03:23.133 --> 1:03:26.134
Well, are you
going to kiss me or what?

1:03:26.361 --> 1:03:29.971
♪♪

1:03:31.975 --> 1:03:33.883
Ooh, my, my, my.

1:03:33.977 --> 1:03:36.127
They're right.

1:03:36.146 --> 1:03:39.481
-Right about what?
-Things do get better with age.

1:03:39.708 --> 1:03:41.465
Oh, yeah. All right.

1:03:41.560 --> 1:03:43.726
-Look out now.
-[both laughing]

1:03:43.821 --> 1:03:46.738
Got you.

1:03:50.661 --> 1:03:53.286
[cheerful jazz music playing]

1:03:57.000 --> 1:04:00.151
I'm glad my massive shoe closet
is helpful to someone.

1:04:00.170 --> 1:04:02.671
Grace:
Oh, my goodness, it's endless.

1:04:02.822 --> 1:04:04.914
You know, I really don't think
it's fair that you're going

1:04:05.067 --> 1:04:07.083
To fancy french quarter party

1:04:07.235 --> 1:04:08.751
And I have to say here,
eating leftovers all by myself.

1:04:08.904 --> 1:04:11.346
Grace: You sound so sad.

1:04:11.573 --> 1:04:13.756
I suppose we've
got leftover booze too.

1:04:13.851 --> 1:04:16.167
A-ha!

1:04:16.186 --> 1:04:20.021
Oh, my god,
that dress is incredible!

1:04:20.248 --> 1:04:22.415
Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

1:04:22.434 --> 1:04:24.267
I mean, keep my shoes
out of the puddles on bourbon,

1:04:24.361 --> 1:04:27.345
But honestly,
you can do whatever you want.

1:04:27.439 --> 1:04:31.941
Oh, you know, I just-- I really,
I really want to look beautiful.

1:04:32.035 --> 1:04:33.426
Anthony's whole family
is going to be there,

1:04:33.519 --> 1:04:35.945
And I just, I want to fit in.

1:04:36.039 --> 1:04:38.022
You and anthony
looked pretty cozy last night.

1:04:38.041 --> 1:04:42.619
But this time his whole family
is going to be there.

1:04:42.713 --> 1:04:46.047
You know, sometimes family isn't
the people we're born into.

1:04:46.199 --> 1:04:48.441
It's the people we pick,

1:04:48.460 --> 1:04:50.293
And they're going
to pick you just like I did.

1:04:50.387 --> 1:04:52.554
Now you know
I don't do all that mushy stuff.

1:04:52.705 --> 1:04:54.614
Oh, I know.

1:04:54.633 --> 1:04:56.966
I love you, too.
You don't have to say it.

1:04:57.119 --> 1:04:59.953
I feel it. Now, go get dressed.

1:04:59.971 --> 1:05:02.046
Listen, please make sure
you don't eat all

1:05:02.065 --> 1:05:04.290
The challah while I'm gone.
-No promises.

1:05:04.384 --> 1:05:05.734
-Okay.
-[phone buzzes]

1:05:05.961 --> 1:05:07.235
Oh, hold on.

1:05:08.739 --> 1:05:09.738
What's wrong?

1:05:12.075 --> 1:05:16.319
I, um, I just got a text.
[chuckles]

1:05:16.413 --> 1:05:19.563
The toronto job is a go.

1:05:19.583 --> 1:05:21.917
Well, what are you going to do?

1:05:23.754 --> 1:05:25.420
I don't know.

1:05:29.000 --> 1:05:31.818
So, is grace going
to be here tonight?

1:05:31.836 --> 1:05:33.503
I need a new dance partner

1:05:33.655 --> 1:05:35.931
Since dad is always
stepping on my feet.

1:05:36.082 --> 1:05:38.158
Yes, uh... [laughs] yes.

1:05:38.176 --> 1:05:40.084
Yes, she is going
to be there tonight.

1:05:40.178 --> 1:05:41.269
That's why your uncle
can't stop taking measurements

1:05:41.421 --> 1:05:43.513
Of the door frame.

1:05:43.607 --> 1:05:45.941
Actually, he's got
a very important errand to run.

1:05:46.168 --> 1:05:47.776
-And then a party to get to.
-Mm-hmm.

1:05:48.003 --> 1:05:50.170
You can't miss
the family picture.

1:05:50.263 --> 1:05:51.671
Oh, he won't. No, he won't.

1:05:51.764 --> 1:05:53.173
'cause everyone will be there.

1:05:53.191 --> 1:05:55.175
What's that?

1:05:55.193 --> 1:05:57.177
Nothing. Just talking
about your date tonight.

1:05:57.195 --> 1:05:59.345
The only date
anyone should be talking

1:05:59.364 --> 1:06:01.957
About up in here is mine.

1:06:02.184 --> 1:06:03.683
You know, grandma,
you are absolutely right.

1:06:03.702 --> 1:06:04.608
-You look beautiful.
-Hm, thank you.

1:06:04.628 --> 1:06:06.294
[doorbell rings]

1:06:06.521 --> 1:06:08.705
Ooh, I have to run.
My date is here.

1:06:08.857 --> 1:06:10.540
He better be
good to you tonight.

1:06:10.634 --> 1:06:12.968
Don't worry, he'll bring me
back at a decent hour.

1:06:14.137 --> 1:06:15.786
My latest batch.

1:06:15.880 --> 1:06:17.864
Mm, almost there, anthony.

1:06:17.882 --> 1:06:19.699
Maybe it needs more water?

1:06:19.792 --> 1:06:22.293
Water? You put water
in pralines?

1:06:22.312 --> 1:06:24.053
Oh, no, baby.

1:06:24.147 --> 1:06:25.796
Keep trying, bro.

1:06:25.816 --> 1:06:27.707
I don't want
to keep marcel waiting.

1:06:27.726 --> 1:06:29.818
I'll see you guys
at the par-tay. Goodbye.

1:06:34.324 --> 1:06:36.324
[sighs]

1:06:36.551 --> 1:06:40.328
They grow up so fast,
don't they, uncle anthony?

1:06:42.891 --> 1:06:45.316
[jazz rendition of
"jingle bells" playing]

1:06:45.335 --> 1:06:47.919
♪♪

1:07:02.427 --> 1:07:05.078
You look...

1:07:05.096 --> 1:07:09.582
[laughing]
is anthony brown speechless?

1:07:09.675 --> 1:07:11.192
I never thought I'd see the day.

1:07:11.344 --> 1:07:13.436
-I am not speechless.
-Mm-hm.

1:07:13.530 --> 1:07:16.197
I'm just looking
for some of the million words

1:07:16.349 --> 1:07:18.091
To describe how you look.
-[laughs]

1:07:18.109 --> 1:07:20.610
Well, I'm going
to need you to find your words

1:07:20.704 --> 1:07:23.038
And, uh, do it quickly because
you're making me nervous.

1:07:24.207 --> 1:07:25.206
Like christmas.

1:07:27.210 --> 1:07:29.210
Like christmas? Please explain.

1:07:32.049 --> 1:07:34.382
You look the way
christmas makes people feel,

1:07:34.534 --> 1:07:39.612
All warm and beautiful
and absolutely perfect.

1:07:39.631 --> 1:07:42.131
I'm not used
to compliments like that.

1:07:42.225 --> 1:07:44.225
Get used to it.
They're coming all night long.

1:07:44.452 --> 1:07:49.314
Oh, let me find out
you're secretly a softie.

1:07:50.809 --> 1:07:52.975
Don't tell anybody. I do
have a reputation to protect.

1:07:53.128 --> 1:07:55.128
-Oh! [laughs]
-shall we?

1:07:55.146 --> 1:07:56.321
We shall.

1:07:57.407 --> 1:08:02.077
♪♪

1:08:04.414 --> 1:08:06.081
You were right.

1:08:06.232 --> 1:08:07.974
You sure know much more
than me about young love.

1:08:08.067 --> 1:08:10.251
Do you think people our age

1:08:10.403 --> 1:08:15.072
Could find something like that?
Or do you think it's too late?

1:08:15.092 --> 1:08:19.427
Well, loretta, you should know,
it's never too late.

1:08:19.579 --> 1:08:20.929
Not for love.

1:08:22.432 --> 1:08:23.765
A dance?

1:08:25.602 --> 1:08:27.418
Of course, marcel.

1:08:27.512 --> 1:08:30.105
[playing "deck the halls"]

1:08:33.335 --> 1:08:34.758
<i> ♪ deck the halls</i>
<i> with boughs of holly ♪</i>

1:08:34.778 --> 1:08:37.445
♪♪

1:08:37.597 --> 1:08:39.763
<i>♪ 'tis the season to be jolly ♪</i>

1:08:39.783 --> 1:08:42.433
♪♪

1:08:42.452 --> 1:08:44.786
<i> ♪ don we now our gay apparel ♪</i>

1:08:44.937 --> 1:08:46.621
<i>♪ fa-la-la, la-la-la, la-la-la ♪</i>

1:08:46.772 --> 1:08:49.365
That's out there, right?

1:08:49.517 --> 1:08:50.542
You having a good time, honey?

1:08:51.853 --> 1:08:53.545
There are so many people here.

1:08:55.707 --> 1:08:58.216
-I wish mom could see.
-I know, honey.

1:09:00.786 --> 1:09:02.137
Well, you stay here
with grandma.

1:09:03.698 --> 1:09:05.306
I have
a little surprise for you.

1:09:05.533 --> 1:09:07.383
What is it?

1:09:07.477 --> 1:09:08.643
Wouldn't be surprised
if I told you now, would it?

1:09:14.467 --> 1:09:16.542
[both laugh]

1:09:16.561 --> 1:09:18.802
["hark! The herald angels sing"
playing]

1:09:18.822 --> 1:09:25.326
♪♪

1:09:25.553 --> 1:09:27.996
-And that's my uncle wilbur.
-Uh-huh.

1:09:28.147 --> 1:09:31.224
And next to him, those are
my cousins, amani and nick.

1:09:31.317 --> 1:09:33.418
Wow. That's a lot of people.

1:09:35.488 --> 1:09:36.838
You aren't going to run
out on me again, are you?

1:09:38.900 --> 1:09:40.175
No.

1:09:41.403 --> 1:09:43.327
I'm not going anywhere.

1:09:43.346 --> 1:09:45.180
This is going
to be an amazing night.

1:09:47.258 --> 1:09:49.517
Yes, it is. I can feel it.

1:09:51.354 --> 1:09:53.104
I'm glad I get
to spend it with you.

1:09:54.840 --> 1:09:56.191
May I have this dance?

1:09:57.843 --> 1:09:59.527
Absolutely.

1:10:01.364 --> 1:10:05.366
♪♪

1:10:07.704 --> 1:10:10.780
[phone buzzing]

1:10:10.932 --> 1:10:20.030
[dramatic music playing]

1:10:20.124 --> 1:10:21.607
[indistinct conversations]

1:10:21.626 --> 1:10:23.960
You are a pretty
good dancer, mr. Brown.

1:10:24.112 --> 1:10:25.778
You should see my samba.

1:10:25.871 --> 1:10:27.371
-Oh, your samba?
-My samba.

1:10:27.465 --> 1:10:28.965
I would love to see that.

1:10:29.117 --> 1:10:30.616
-You will see that.
-Mm.

1:10:30.635 --> 1:10:35.288
[indistinct conversations]

1:10:35.381 --> 1:10:37.139
Mom, have you seen charlene?

1:10:37.292 --> 1:10:38.716
I'm sure she's here somewhere.

1:10:38.735 --> 1:10:39.817
Okay.

1:10:41.963 --> 1:10:42.979
I'm gonna go ask anthony.

1:10:43.073 --> 1:10:43.988
No, no.

1:10:45.057 --> 1:10:46.074
Let them have their fun.

1:10:47.819 --> 1:10:50.319
[sighs]
yeah, I guess you're right.

1:10:50.413 --> 1:10:51.996
[both laughing]

1:10:54.158 --> 1:10:55.750
How was that for a start?

1:10:56.736 --> 1:10:58.311
-Very good.
-Yeah.

1:10:58.329 --> 1:11:01.256
You are definitely
full of surprises.

1:11:04.319 --> 1:11:06.486
I'm sure she's getting
dressed somewhere.

1:11:06.504 --> 1:11:08.263
I know, I just-- I don't wanna
miss the family photo, you know?

1:11:10.249 --> 1:11:11.516
I'll help you look for her.

1:11:14.512 --> 1:11:17.939
[upbeat jazz music playing]

1:11:28.618 --> 1:11:30.434
So do you have any
weird childhood sweethearts

1:11:30.528 --> 1:11:31.619
Hiding around here?

1:11:31.771 --> 1:11:34.104
Oh. I wouldn't know.

1:11:34.124 --> 1:11:36.699
-Oh?
-I've only been looking at you.

1:11:36.851 --> 1:11:38.701
Mm. Perfect answer.
[laughs]

1:11:38.795 --> 1:11:41.629
♪♪

1:11:57.889 --> 1:12:02.150
Give me just a few minutes?

1:12:02.301 --> 1:12:03.484
Absolutely.

1:12:04.896 --> 1:12:07.322
-Don't go far.
-I won't.

1:12:09.734 --> 1:12:11.159
-Hey, jordan.
-Hey.

1:12:11.310 --> 1:12:13.143
May I have this dance?

1:12:13.237 --> 1:12:14.904
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

1:12:14.998 --> 1:12:16.146
Okay.

1:12:16.166 --> 1:12:19.000
♪♪

1:12:25.066 --> 1:12:26.566
Moving pretty good!

1:12:27.177 --> 1:12:29.844
[music continues in distance]

1:12:37.687 --> 1:12:40.429
[line ringing]

1:12:40.582 --> 1:12:42.431
<i> Hi, it's charlene.</i>

1:12:42.525 --> 1:12:44.692
<i> I'm not here right now.</i>
<i> Leave me a message.</i>

1:12:50.925 --> 1:12:53.593
Oh, this party is so much fun.

1:12:53.611 --> 1:12:58.188
Oh, my goodness,
miss loretta, it is incredible.

1:12:58.208 --> 1:13:01.100
Your family
is just so wonderful,

1:13:01.193 --> 1:13:02.377
And thank you for having me.

1:13:03.621 --> 1:13:05.605
Can I show you something?

1:13:05.623 --> 1:13:06.714
Of course.

1:13:08.885 --> 1:13:10.051
Okay.

1:13:14.557 --> 1:13:18.041
-Is that my house?
-Yes, ma'am.

1:13:18.061 --> 1:13:21.562
It's a little bit
of old new orleans,

1:13:21.714 --> 1:13:24.565
With a little bit of modern,
and a little bit of anthony.

1:13:24.792 --> 1:13:27.551
And a lot of you.
Look, I have something for you.

1:13:27.570 --> 1:13:30.053
What?

1:13:30.148 --> 1:13:32.240
-Come over here, baby.
-Okay.

1:13:32.391 --> 1:13:35.410
Here it is, right here.
Let me hold your purse.

1:13:35.561 --> 1:13:36.894
-Oh, thank you so much.
-But you have to open it.

1:13:36.913 --> 1:13:39.972
Okay. [gasps]

1:13:40.065 --> 1:13:43.826
Miss loretta, it's beautiful.

1:13:43.978 --> 1:13:46.570
I make them every christmas
for everyone in the family.

1:13:46.664 --> 1:13:48.423
But I'm--I'm not, um...

1:13:50.168 --> 1:13:52.260
But I didn't--
I didn't get you anything,

1:13:52.487 --> 1:13:53.928
But you did.

1:13:54.155 --> 1:13:57.657
You gave me more
than I could ever imagine.

1:13:57.675 --> 1:13:59.583
My grandson always
thought that working

1:13:59.602 --> 1:14:01.436
Would make a life worth living.

1:14:01.663 --> 1:14:04.105
But you, my dear,
you brought him back home,

1:14:04.256 --> 1:14:06.089
Back to the family.

1:14:06.109 --> 1:14:09.168
He's so lucky
to have family like you.

1:14:09.261 --> 1:14:11.112
And we're lucky to have you.

1:14:11.263 --> 1:14:13.948
And you know what?
I've got to go find my boo thing

1:14:14.099 --> 1:14:16.099
Before my cousins, they're gonna
think it's open season.

1:14:16.119 --> 1:14:17.843
Please let me grab this purse.

1:14:17.937 --> 1:14:19.436
-Take your purse, bye, boo.
-Bye!

1:14:19.456 --> 1:14:21.772
-Oh boy, don't hurt him.
-I will.

1:14:21.866 --> 1:14:26.519
-He is so happy.
-[laughs]

1:14:26.537 --> 1:14:28.204
I see you got
my grandmother's gift.

1:14:28.298 --> 1:14:32.374
You are so lucky
to have such a great family.

1:14:32.469 --> 1:14:34.543
But why didn't you tell me?
You didn't even warn me.

1:14:34.696 --> 1:14:36.862
I didn't have anything for her.

1:14:36.881 --> 1:14:38.698
She wanted you to have it.

1:14:38.716 --> 1:14:40.382
You know, she wants you
to feel like part

1:14:40.477 --> 1:14:43.369
Of the celebration,
and part of the family.

1:14:43.387 --> 1:14:47.130
All right, folks.
Now, we have one more song,

1:14:47.150 --> 1:14:50.392
And then it's time for
the annual brown family photo!

1:14:50.545 --> 1:14:52.211
[laughs] a one, two...

1:14:52.304 --> 1:14:54.155
-Oh, charlene.
-What? Huh?

1:14:54.382 --> 1:14:55.881
-Um, I got to go. Excuse me.
-Wait. Huh?

1:14:55.900 --> 1:14:57.383
Excuse me.

1:14:57.401 --> 1:14:58.809
[sighs]

1:14:58.828 --> 1:15:04.832
♪♪

1:15:05.059 --> 1:15:07.251
Anthony, anthony, hey.
Uh, where's charlene?

1:15:09.655 --> 1:15:11.005
Wait. Where's my wife?

1:15:13.993 --> 1:15:15.176
Charlene, my wife, you're
supposed to picked her up.

1:15:15.327 --> 1:15:16.736
-Where is she?
-[car door slams]

1:15:16.754 --> 1:15:18.754
-My wife--
-charlene.

1:15:18.848 --> 1:15:21.498
Charlene, baby.

1:15:21.592 --> 1:15:24.426
Hey, baby! [laughs]

1:15:24.579 --> 1:15:26.687
Oh, oh, I missed you.

1:15:26.839 --> 1:15:28.748
Mm. I missed you more.

1:15:28.841 --> 1:15:30.099
-Oh, you look so good.
-Oh, thanks.

1:15:30.251 --> 1:15:33.343
-Hi!
-Oh, hi. I am so sorry.

1:15:33.437 --> 1:15:35.104
How could you forget? I reminded
you over a hundred times.

1:15:35.256 --> 1:15:37.439
I took a cab. It's okay.

1:15:37.534 --> 1:15:38.533
Yep, but you told me you was
gonna get her.

1:15:38.760 --> 1:15:40.201
I was up in the party
all night.

1:15:40.352 --> 1:15:42.444
It's fine, christopher. I heard
you got a new girlfriend.

1:15:42.539 --> 1:15:46.023
-Did you get jordan's gift?
-It's in the car.

1:15:46.042 --> 1:15:48.042
She doesn't need
a gift until christmas.

1:15:48.193 --> 1:15:49.693
Chris, you know love
gets folks distracted sometimes,

1:15:49.712 --> 1:15:52.121
You should know.

1:15:52.273 --> 1:15:54.290
Hey, I don't want you guys
to think that I'm not pulling

1:15:54.442 --> 1:15:56.442
My weight around here.

1:15:56.460 --> 1:15:58.702
I just-- I'm trying to be
a part of more things here.

1:15:58.796 --> 1:16:00.221
Nobody thinks that you're
not pulling your weight, man.

1:16:00.448 --> 1:16:03.632
