do this too many times.

1:20:29.050 --> 1:20:31.808
Come on. We're going for a walk.

1:20:31.828 --> 1:20:34.219
I have all this
packing to do still.

1:20:34.238 --> 1:20:35.721
It'll be there.

1:20:35.739 --> 1:20:39.058
[sighs] okay, fine.
Where are we going?

1:20:39.076 --> 1:20:42.895
You know, grace, we have
a saying here in new orleans.

1:20:42.988 --> 1:20:45.080
-What?
-Guys are like streetcars.

1:20:45.174 --> 1:20:47.324
[laughter]

1:20:47.343 --> 1:20:51.753
One is coming around
the corner every few minutes.

1:20:51.848 --> 1:20:54.923
[gasps]

1:20:55.076 --> 1:20:57.852
[uplifting music playing]

1:21:04.268 --> 1:21:07.677
What? What is this?

1:21:07.771 --> 1:21:11.848
Grace hill, I need you to
know that you belong right here

1:21:11.942 --> 1:21:15.094
In new orleans with me.

1:21:15.112 --> 1:21:16.595
Anthony--

1:21:16.688 --> 1:21:18.706
My grandma--she has a saying.

1:21:18.933 --> 1:21:21.433
She says,
"family is who you choose."

1:21:21.526 --> 1:21:24.211
I'm standing here
and I'm choosing you.

1:21:25.956 --> 1:21:27.882
[grace exhales]

1:21:28.109 --> 1:21:29.341
I used to...

1:21:32.555 --> 1:21:36.682
Believe that I didn't want
to be attached to any place.

1:21:38.728 --> 1:21:39.685
Or anyone.

1:21:42.640 --> 1:21:47.735
But your beautiful family... Has
shown me something different.

1:21:50.406 --> 1:21:52.072
Grace, I know that
you are so good on your own.

1:21:53.743 --> 1:21:56.135
I know that you have
independence and you--

1:21:56.153 --> 1:21:58.561
You don't actually need me.

1:21:58.656 --> 1:22:00.080
Could you want me?

1:22:01.992 --> 1:22:04.810
Yeah. Yeah.

1:22:04.828 --> 1:22:06.828
Yeah, I do.

1:22:06.923 --> 1:22:08.923
Do you think you could
find room in your heart

1:22:09.074 --> 1:22:12.092
For me and this big family
of mine that loves you?

1:22:19.009 --> 1:22:20.392
Well...

1:22:25.424 --> 1:22:27.107
That depends.

1:22:27.259 --> 1:22:29.668
Depends on what?

1:22:29.761 --> 1:22:31.403
Do I get to ride
a streetcar, too?

1:22:32.782 --> 1:22:35.674
[laughs]

1:22:35.693 --> 1:22:39.027
One second,
I always wanted to do this.

1:22:39.180 --> 1:22:41.121
-All aboard!
-[laughs]

1:22:41.273 --> 1:22:43.940
[cheers and applause]

1:22:44.034 --> 1:22:46.126
This is so perfect.

1:22:46.278 --> 1:22:48.462
[laughter]

1:22:48.613 --> 1:22:49.964
[indistinct conversations]

1:22:50.115 --> 1:22:52.207
Tina: Welcome to
the family, grace!

1:22:52.301 --> 1:22:55.377
Okay, what do you think?

1:22:55.471 --> 1:22:59.031
I can't believe
you got me a whole streetcar.

1:22:59.124 --> 1:23:01.700
[laughs]
just like the story.

1:23:01.719 --> 1:23:04.369
You know, a very wise woman
once told me

1:23:04.388 --> 1:23:07.889
That sometimes
the old ways are the best ways.

1:23:08.042 --> 1:23:09.891
-And the most romantic.
-And the most romantic.

1:23:09.986 --> 1:23:11.710
Mm-hmm.

1:23:11.729 --> 1:23:15.472
[gasps] it's her! It's her!

1:23:15.491 --> 1:23:17.658
